title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 11 dozen.

title: beef stew
directions: Wipe beef with damp cloth.
Roll meat in flour; brown in fat in heavy saucepan.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat until almost tender, about 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion until brown.
Drain.
Add refried beans and large salsa.
Keep warm.
Spread crushed taco chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture over chips and top with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 or 3 layers, 23 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: donelda's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add rest of ingredients in order given. (May add chopped onion, if desired.)
Heat through.
Serve on buns.

title: dakota eggs
directions: Fry bacon cubes in a skillet until brown and crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
In a bowl, beat together eggs and corn.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over bacon cubes and cook until eggs are set and lightly browned underneath.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix eggs, shortening and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add cream or milk; blend well.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder; sift together.
Add to mixture; beat well.
Add bananas and blend with other mixture.
Add nuts last.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and add your icing.

title: sugar tacos(yields 3 dozen)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, together.
Sift the flour and add to the mixture.
Let the mixture set for 3 hours.

title: meal in one
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: frozen golden punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups hot water and cool.
Add sugar to
2 cups
boiling
water,
then cool.
Mix all together and freeze.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Vegetables may be steamed to desired tenderness.
Cool and combine with dressing. Toss well and cover.
Best if chilled for at least 2 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with the salt and cracked ice; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
To the pickles, add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then seal in hot jars.
Yields 8 pints.

title: applesauce  muffins
directions: Mix applesauce and soda and set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add to butter mixture.
Add nuts and applesauce mix.
Cover and store in refrigerator until needed.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine egg whites, yogurt, applesauce, oil and zest; add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: zwiebach or dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; add sugar and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, beating slowly, then yeast mixture and flour, until thickened.
Let rise in warm oven or surface.
Punch down and put in pans.
Bake at 350° until finished.

title: raspberry applesauce
directions: In a large bowl, mix boiling water into dry Jell-O until dissolved.
Stir in applesauce. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix sugar, dry mustard, bacon and catsup.
Add beans and stir. Bake at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Shake chicken juices in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter and oil.
Place browned chicken in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine orange juice with vinegar, sugar, basil and nutmeg and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Baste often, then place peach or apricot halves between chicken pieces.
Baste well and bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; beat with mixer until frothy. Fold in sour cream and pineapple.
Chill.
Add some cherries before chilling, if desired.
This called for maraschino, but I couldn't find sugar-free.

title: bailey's irish creme
directions: In blender, at low speed, blend all ingredients until smooth. Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Stir or shake before serving.
Great over ice or in coffee.
Or make "Buttery Nipples" by mixing 1 1/2 parts Baileys with 1/2 part Butterscotch Schnapps.
Yummy!!!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
In another bowl mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture.	Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: cranberry cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and lemon peel.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat half the crumbs into bottom of 9-inch spring form pan (sides removed).
Bake at 400 degrees about 8 minutes or until golden.
Cool.
Attach sides of pan.
Butter sides and pat on remaining crumbs.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Mix well, then stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and set aside.
Cook cranberries according to directions.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add celery, apples and nuts.
Then add Jell-O.
Pour in salad bowl or salad mold and chill in refrigerator.

title: cheesecakes
directions: Mix together the crust ingredients.
Place 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoon in cup.
(Put Baggie over shot glass and press crumbs down.)

title: five minute fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits thoroughly, saving 1 cupful of juice.
Mix juice, fruit, lemon juice and pudding mix together and stir.
Chill. Just before serving, slice banana into it.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook soup, milk, onion, celery and green chilies until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken pieces.
Heat until completely hot, stirring often. Then fold in sour cream.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese and broken potato chips on top.
Heat enough to melt cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar.
Add a dash of salt, corn syrup, butter and pecan halves.
Pour into the unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in oven at 350° until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: black cherry mold
directions: Drain cherries; save juice.
Dilute Jell-O with 6 cups water (3 hot and 3 cold).
Use 1 cup cherry juice to make 7 cups.
Place bowl in refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Mix in softened Cool Whip and cherries.
Coat the mold pan with whipped cream.
Pour Jell-O into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff mushroom caps.
Spray glass pan with non-stick oil.
Bake in a 350 degree preheated oven for 15 minutes.

title: coconut crumb cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar; mix in butter until mealy.
Mix 1 cup of mixture with 3/4 cup coconut (reserve).
To the rest of the mixture add 3/4 cup coconut, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir together the milk and soda; add this to the mixture. Add egg and mix well with spoon.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix in flour.
Add cream, milk, broth, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese.
When melted, add green beans.
Pour mixture into casserole dish; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Stir together flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour mixture.
Turn meat and flour other side. Cut meat into 6 serving pieces.
Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Brown meat over medium heat, about 15 minutes.
Cover tightly; simmer 1 hour.
Add a small amount of water if necessary. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly. Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wash rice.
Pour over bottom of pan. Put chicken pieces over rice, then sprinkle over the soup mix. Mix soup and water together.
Pour over.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.
(First hour, cover pan.)

title: cookie's own sauce
directions: Sieve tomatoes into 4-quart heavy kettle.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, bay leaf, cinnamon, basil, garlic and meat, poultry and sausage seasoning.
Also all pork hock.
Cook slowly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs and milk.
Mix other ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Mix in chicken after refrigeration.
Bake at 350° to 400°.
When about through baking, top with cheese.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lay 6 chicken breasts in roaster pan with 3 1/2 cups of water and 1 stick melted margarine.
Pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add milk and eggs.
Add flour, baking cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Beat everything together by hand until creamy and smooth.
Drop by large tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Watch carefully to not overbake.
Cool on wire racks.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: delicious salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and cherry juice.
Add cherries and pineapple with juice, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Garnish with chopped nuts and bits of cherries.
Sets up quickly.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef; add salt and pepper if you wish.
Drain beef when done.
Mix soup and milk together. Put beef in casserole dish (sprayed with non sticking spray). Pour soup mixture on top of beef.
Put cheese slices on top of mixture. Then top with Tater Tots.
Bake in oven until Tater Tots are golden brown.
Serve with vegetables.

title: four way chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, skin side down.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low heat until dissolved.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, turning once and basting frequently until covered with a rich brown sauce.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, beef and rice; stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover tightly; simmer for 25 minutes.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup with cut asparagus.
Place in casserole dish.
Place asparagus spears on top, then cover with cheese slices for the final topping.
Heat for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 450 degrees until brown.

title: rave review cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in mixer. Add coconut and
pecans.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crunchy catfish
directions: Combine salad dressing and seasoning blend.
Spread mixture on both sides of fish.
Dredge in crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger.
Mix sauce with meat.
Cook noodles and drain. In baking dish, rotate sauce and noodles, starting with and ending with sauce.
Sprinkle both cheeses on top of sauce.
Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown.

title: miniature fruitcakes
directions: Grease and flour 36 medium muffin cups.
In large bowl stir together fruit, dates and nuts.
In medium bowl stir flour, powder and salt.

title: lemon drops(1855)
directions: Pour enough lemon juice into the powdered sugar to dissolve it. Cook to hard-crack stage or 275°.
Drop onto buttered cookie sheet to cool and harden.

title: another dip
directions: Mix well and use as dip for fruit you like.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together and bake in 11 x 7 pan at 350° until done. While still warm, make icing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and broth. Heat and stir until smooth and hot.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese. Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and mix it with chicken broth, cream of celery and cream of chicken soup.
Steam vegetables until barely cooked; add salt.
In large casserole dish, alternate layers of vegetables, chicken mixture, mushrooms and bread crumbs twice. Sprinkle very lightly with curry powder.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: l.b.j. dessert
directions: For crust, mix butter, flour and 1 cup pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at
350° for 20 minutes. Cool and set aside.

title: great potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes and margarine; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Use 1/2 cup M&M's for top of cookies.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese in pieces.
Brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; add eggs, flour and cheese pieces.
Turn into prepared shell.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining slices of cheese.
Bake 3 minutes longer.
Cut into slices.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, flour, soda and salt well.
Raisins and pecans may be added.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs and vegetable oil and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator.
Bake as desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Add bananas; mix well.
Pour mixture into two 8-inch square pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: baked garlic chicken
directions: Soften butter or oleo; add garlic that's peeled and crushed, lemon rind and spices.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Loosen chicken skin, starting at neck, working under skin all over breast and legs; remove excess fat.
Now using fingers again, apply garlic butter to chicken meat under skin all over.
Put lemon slices and 10 unpeeled garlic cloves inside bird.
Salt and pepper inside and out well. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Baste if you want.
Serve with French bread.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine all juices and water. Add mashed bananas. Mix well and freeze. Before serving, take out of freezer and leave in refrigerator for 5 to 6 hours. Pour ginger ale over frozen punch. Yields 20 to 25 servings.

title: ham gravy
directions: Melt butter in a medium sauce pan over medium heat. Add flour and beef extract. Mix thoroughly. Slowly add water. Cook until smooth and thick. Add sherry to taste.

title: haw marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken, beef or pork and let stand overnight.
Great for cooking on grill.

title: pumpkin-oat bran muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine pumpkin and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans, coated with cooking spray, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remove from pans immediately; serve warm or at room temperature. Yield:
1 dozen (about 138 calories each).
Protein 4.3.
Fat 3.6. Carb. 22.5.
Choles. 0.
Iron 1.6.
Sodium 117.
Calcium 70.

title: val's apple tart
directions: Put the cookie dough onto pizza pan and roll out.
Bake according to directions; cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla flavoring and spread on top of cooled cookie crust.
Slice the apples and put on top of mixture. Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Pour the ice cream topping over the apples. Sprinkle top with peanuts.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually add water.
Heat quickly to boiling.
Lower heat and cook slowly for 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.

title: mushroom delight
directions: Fry bacon; cool and crumble.
Mix with cream cheese.
Clean mushrooms with damp paper towel.
Remove mushroom stems and chop fine.
Mix with cream cheese mixture.
Stuff mushrooms; sprinkle with garlic salt and broil in oven until nicely browned.
Serve immediately.

title: oreo delight
directions: Break cookies into pieces and place a layer of cookies into deep dish, then add a layer of vanilla ice cream. Top with whipped topping and place in freezer.

title: applesauce bread pudding
directions: Soak raisins in hot water to plump.
Combine eggs, sugar, applesauce and milk.
Stir in butter, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Tear bread into 1-inch pieces and add until bread is coated (you can use bread ends).

title: kheema mattar(a mild ground beef curry)
directions: Fry onion in oil, add garlic and ginger; stir.
Add turmeric and chili powder.
Add hamburger meat and cook through.
Stir in yogurt and peas.
Cook 15 minutes, simmer on low.
Add garam masala and salt.
Garnish with chili and coriander.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos with rolling pin.
Reserve about 1 cup.
Spread remainder of crumbs in a rectangular pan.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over crumbs; mix well.
Press into pan.
Chill.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/2 jar salsa.
Spread on bottom of pie plate.
Top with the other 1/2 of the salsa and the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine syrup and peanut butter. Stir in Rice Krispies.
These can be dropped from teaspoon on waxed paper to set overnight or can be eaten immediately.

title: caesar salad
directions: You will need a glass jar with lid.

title: farmhouse roast pork
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Cut deep slits in the pork roast with a knife and insert the garlic slivers. Put the pork in a shallow roasting pan and set aside.

title: lemon delight
directions: Blend and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°; cool.

title: knot cookies
directions: Combine and mix well eggs, sugar, vanilla, orange juice and grated rind, sifted flour and baking powder.
Roll dough in strips pencil thin, more or less as you choose.
Tie into knots.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool cookies and dip into glaze made from powdered sugar, milk and drop of essence (vanilla, lemon, orange or whatever).
For a more festive appearance, sprinkle with colored sprinkles or chocolate shot over glaze.

title: skoby's creamed corn
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except butter and crumbs, for 20 minutes.
Mix butter and crumbs and sprinkle on top of mixture. Lightly toast for a few minutes in oven.

title: brussels sprouts in blue cheese sauce
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts as directed on package.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and salt, mixing until smooth.
Cook over low heat about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring until well blended.
Return to heat and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add 1 cup milk; bring to boil and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: milk chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter or margarine, milk and chocolate in a saucepan; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar; beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla; spread on cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir in Ro-Tel.
(May add a little hot sauce if not hot enough.)
Good with Ritz crackers, chips, etc.

title: beefy mac and cheese
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion.
Saute and drain fat.
Blend tomato sauce, water, oregano and salt with meat and onions.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In casserole dish layer macaroni, half beef and sauce and half cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange congealed fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello by directions on box.
While still hot, add marshmallows and stir until cooled.
When cooled, stir in pineapple, whipped cream, coconut and cherries.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until congealed.
Serves 15.

title: pears helene
directions: Peel pear.
Cut in half and scoop out core.
Bring water and sugar to a boil in a skillet, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add pears.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until pears are tender.
Turn only once.
Stir in vanilla. Cool pears in liquid in refrigerator.
Place 1/2 cup ice cream in 2 dessert dishes.
Top with a pear half.
Drizzle fudge topping over the pears.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
If using fresh onion and green pepper, saute until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot on low.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add confectioners sugar and cocoa which have been sifted together.
Add egg yolks and salt.
Cream until thoroughly blended.
Blend in vanilla and milk.
Cream until of spreading consistency.
Yield: frosting for two 8-inch or 9-inch layers.

title: sour cream coconut layer cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together and chill.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix apple filling and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and butter; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, butter, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Spoon on pie filling.
Cover with the rest of batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside. Measure bran flakes and milk into mixing bowl.
Stir to combine. Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.

title: onion pie
directions: Cut
bacon
into
small
pieces
and
fry until cooked. Remove from
pan.
Add sliced onions to bacon grease and cook until soft.
Add cooked bacon.
Sprinkle on flour.
Mix.
Beat egg and milk; add egg and milk mixture.
Stir and cook slightly until
it thickens.
Add to pie shell.
Bake at 400°for 30 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on cookie sheet until brown.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Valley Ranch and put over crust.
Apply veggies of your choice and cheese.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Makes 17 cups mix.
Add 3 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Put Eagle Brand in a bowl, add lemon juice, then crushed pineapple, pecans and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry bars
directions: In small bowl, blend all ingredients well.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Toast pecans lightly in oven.
Cook as a syrup: sugar, orange juice, orange rind and salt.
Cook at 238° to soft ball stage. Stir well.
Then add nuts, taking care not to break.
Stir until syrup begins to sugar.
Lift out pieces, one at a time.
Place on waxed paper.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Spread 2 cups of spaghetti sauce over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large skillet, brown sausage with onion over medium heat.
Drain.
Add bread crumbs, salt, basil, pepper, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese and egg.
Mix together.
Cut each lasagne noodle in half crosswise.
Spread 2 to 3 tablespoons of sausage mixture evenly on each half.
Roll up from shorter side and place seam down in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: In skillet on medium heat, combine margarine, chopped onion (almost browned), bacon (cut in pieces) and ground beef (brown, do not drain). Add pork and beans, mustard and ketchup, mixing well. Begin adding brown sugar. Add to suit your taste. Simmer on medium to low heat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: *If the chili peppers aren't hot enough, add a dash of cayenne pepper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all together and spread over chicken.

title: circus salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple and Mandarin oranges, then add to Jell-O mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
(Chopped nuts and marshmallows can be added, if desired.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook all day outside in a big wash pot.

title: shrimp-potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over salad greens. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add 1/2 stick margarine. Add chopped and cubed Velveeta cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush crackers.
Add 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Mix and spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Combine first four ingredients and cook until thickened, then add vinegar, butter, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in small saucepan over medium-high heat and bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: open devil burgers
directions: Toast 12 slices of bread and spread each slice with meat mixture to the very edge.
Broil about 3-inches from heat for about 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain. Add Ragu, tomato paste and spices.
Cook spinach as directed. Drain liquid off of spinach and add to mixture.
Cover and simmer meat mixture for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook spiral pasta almost done; drain and place in large baking dish (sprayed with Pam).
Mix slightly beaten eggs, cooked spinach and
1 cup of cheese with pasta.
Pour meat mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes, or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for about 4 hours.
Stir frequently so it doesn't stick.
Serve over rice.

title: eggplant nicoise
directions: Split eggplant in half lengthwise and gently scoop out pulp; dice. Brush inside of the shell with some of the oil. Reserve the rest. Place shells on ungreased baking sheet, cavities up. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Saute garlic and onion in reserved oil until golden. Add eggplant pulp with salt, pepper, parsley and Tabasco. Dice tomato and add (if using canned tomatoes, drain first). Simmer for 10 minutes. Combine crumbs and cheese and fold half into eggplant mixture. Spoon into shells and sprinkle with remaining crumbs and paprika. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook pork sausage until no pink shows.
Combine cornmeal, milk, eggs and corn.
Blend well and set aside.
Crumble sausage.
Add shredded cheese, chopped onion and jalapeno peppers.
Mix well, then add to cornmeal mixture. Pour into a well-oiled 9-inch cast-iron skillet that has been heated.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; melt margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and saute until brown.
Transfer to a shallow baking pan. Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and mix in order.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: passion dock pudding
directions: Boil tender dock leaves with onions.
When cooked, add oatmeal, egg and butter or margarine.
Simmer for half an hour. The nutritive value of this Square Meal recipe would be increased by the inclusion of some yeast extract.
(GR)

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Grate or chop cabbage, celery, green pepper and onion. Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together with gelatin and chill for at least 2 hours.
Great with rye or wheat crackers.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces; place in a medium saucepan. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool. Combine potato, chopped green onions and pimiento in a large bowl; toss gently.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Mix with Jell-O.
Add lemon juice with milk and juice from pineapple.
Total out liquid to 4 cups total with water.
Chill Jell-O.

title: baked beans
directions: If using 20 ounce cans of pork and beans, use only three.

title: fondant(french candy)
directions: Cook until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour out into 2 buttered plates.
Let cool.
Beat until it turns white, then work by hand.
Add nuts and more nuts until it will hold no more.
Make into rolls and slice.
Work up one plate at a time as it sets quickly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet and drain.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Put 3/4 cup crushed potato chips (corn flakes or cracker crumbs may be substituted) in bottom of casserole dish. Pour in hamburger mixture and sprinkle remainder of crushed potato chips on top.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix well.
Add beaten eggs and flavorings.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and nutmeg.
Mix with sugar mixture, stirring well.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, cream sugar with butter, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to creamy mixture.
Chill 1 hour until firm.
On floured surface, roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and place on cookie sheet (greased).
Bake at 370° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 dozen cookies.
Ice or decorate if desired.

title: chicken delish
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pour into a 9-inch greased baking dish. Place cut up pieces of chicken on top of mixture and sprinkle with 1 envelope or less onion soup mix. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°. Don't peek.

title: coq au vin
directions: In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp, remove and drain bacon. Mix flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake 2 or 3 chicken pieces in bag until coated.
Brown chicken in bacon fat; remove to warm platter.
Cut carrots diagonally into 2-inch pieces.
Using same bacon fat, cook and stir mushrooms and onions in Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Place chicken in Dutch oven.
Crumble bacon on chicken and add remaining ingredients. Heat to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until thickest chicken pieces are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Yields 2 servings.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Take out center of potato.
Melt butter; add Tabasco.
Brush melted butter mixture on insides and outsides of potatoes. Place skins on a tray and microwave 2 to 3 minutes.

title: sauteed pea pods
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter for 2 minutes over medium-high heat.
Add pea pods and saute until golden.
Add water and bouillon.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes until pea pods are crisp-tender.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in bowl.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in 9-inch layers.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container; cover and blend on low for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand 5 minutes; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Sauce:
Mix onion, garlic, oregano, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer as spaghetti sauce.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and put into a large heavy pot.
Cover with water.
Add corn, margarine, salt, pepper, onion powder (may use fresh chopped onion), garlic powder and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, but are not mushy.
Turn down on low heat and add soup of your choice and the milk.
Stir until blended, but be careful to not beat up the potatoes.
Serve while hot over corn chips, Mexican cornbread, regular style cornbread or with crackers.

title: old fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add shortening, cutting in with knives.
Beat egg in 1-cup measuring cup, then add milk until 3/4 full.
Add to dry mixture and combine.
(Don't overmix, it will be lumpy.)

title: lavender dates
directions: Mix the lavender and cream cheese and use this mixture to stuff the dates.
Roll each date in granulated sugar.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in margarine; remove chicken.
In skillet, combine soup and seasonings.
Return chicken.
Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat until warm.
Serve over noodles; garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: heart healthy quick chicken and vegetables
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine onion, celery, carrot and butter.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Stir in flour, bouillon granules, marjoram, thyme and pepper.
Blend in water.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring once.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with noodles or spaghetti.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Saute oleo, celery and onion in pan.
Mix all together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Or, cook in crock-pot on high for 45 minutes or on low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Bring oleo and sugar to a rolling boil, about 2 to 3 minutes. Add coconut flavoring and nut meats.
Return to stove and boil another minute.
Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Separate graham crackers and place on sheet.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove crackers to rack to cool.
Store in tight container.
Very good for snacks.

title: mole bars
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter together.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into oiled pan.

title: cream cheese drops
directions: Beat the oleo, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, nuts, milk and vanilla.
Beat ingredients until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Lightly press a chocolate chip into center of each cookie.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine in pan and boil several minutes.
Spices can be tied in cheesecloth.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Remove seed from peppers and chop fine in food processor.
Set aside.
Place in large deep pan the salt, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Mix flour and water in a bowl.
Add to vinegar mixture and stir.
Add peppers.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Put pepper butter in jot jars and seal, but not tight. Place in water bath 5 to 10 minutes, then retighten ring again. Makes about 8 pints.

title: oven "fried okra"
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
In a bowl, beat the egg and Tabasco together.
Combine the bread crumbs with salt and pepper in a separate bowl.
Place the okra in the bowl with the egg mixture and coat it well.
Remove the okra with a slotted spoon, allowing the excess egg to drip back into the bowl.
Then, toss the wet okra in the bread crumb mixture until well coated.
Spread the okra out on the prepared baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Add more salt and pepper if desired.
Continue until all the okra is fried.
Serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Beat in banana and eggs.
Add Bisquick gradually and stir.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cover with foil (lightly) at end until done (30 to 45 minutes).
Wonderful!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash and peel cucumbers and slice in bowl.
Place oil, vinegar, pepper and peppercorns in a mixing bowl and mix together. Place sliced cucumbers in bowl.
Pour over the oil and vinegar mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold as side dish.

title: my pear pie
directions: Take a pan of little knotty pears off my tree.
Peel and cut in tiny slices.
Add water to cover; cook in pot on top of stove. Add 1 cup sugar and a little cinnamon and ground cloves.
While cooking, open a can of biscuits; split the 10 to make 20.
Put lots of butter or oleo in; cook in oven.
When done, split these and add more butter and brown.
Layer with pears.

title: angel apricot salad
directions: Boil pineapple with juice. Add Jell-O. Stir until Jell-O is dissolved. Cool down. Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and salt. Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: grilled stuffed iowa pork chops
directions: Have butcher cut pocket in pork chops.
Fill mixture in pocket.
Insert toothpicks to hold pocket together.
Combine butter, parsley, lemon juice, wine and salt.
Place chops on grill.
Cook about 7 minutes on each side, basting frequently with sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until fine particles are formed.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla.
Add to 1st mixture; blend well. Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll dough out onto floured surface, 1/4 inch thick. Cut with desired cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: grandmother's lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Gradually stir in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Slowly stir at least half of the hot mixture into egg yolks. Then blend hot mixture into saucepan. Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Continue stirring. Blend in margarine and lemon juice. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue; brown and cool.

title: country inn chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch square or round cake pan.
Mix all ingredients together (batter will be very thin) and bake in prepared pan for approximately 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: graham crackers
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Blend the remaining ingredients with a blender in a large bowl.
Add the blender ingredients to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Divide the dough in half and roll out with a rolling pin on a 9-inch floured surface.
Roll as thin as you can.
Let your children help you poke the dough with a fork and then cut it into squares.
Place crackers on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 3 dozen 2-inch crackers.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, then blend in egg.
Add to mixture the flour and vanilla.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in 400° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
If using cookie cutters, chill dough for 20 minutes before cutting.
If decorating, add sugar or sprinkles, etc., before baking.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 2-quart casserole with coarsely crushed Doritos.
Brown meat, add seasoning and 3/4 can tomato sauce. Spread over crushed Doritos.
Mix remaining tomato sauce with refried beans.
Spread over meat layer.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, covered, at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with larger corn chips (grated cheese first), then return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer chicken one hour in salt and water.
Debone.
Prepare broccoli according to package and place in greased, deep casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Prepare sauce by combining soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: *May substitute 1/2 pound butter and 1 cup Crisco.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add next 6 ingredients and mix well. Form into a ball; roll in a mixture of parsley and chopped nuts. Chill; serve with crackers.

title: lychees gelatin
directions: Heat the syrup of lychees plus 1/4 cup water.
Dissolve the gelatin in heated syrup and let cool.
When cool, transfer to Pyrex and mix the cream and milk.
Cut the lychees into 4 pieces and add to mixture.
Freeze until firm for 1 hour.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix soup with milk and pour a little of mixture in bottom of square or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts in pan and cover with a layer of Swiss cheese.
Add remainder of soup.
Put a 1/2-inch layer of dressing on top.
Drop over top with melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans; put in a casserole dish.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Mix and pour over green beans in dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove casserole; add canned onion rings.
Return to oven and let onion rings brown, approximately 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach ball spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach; do not salt.
Drain well and cut up with scissors.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve hot with crackers. Delicious.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften and blend well the first 2 ingredients.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed pecans.

title: sportsmanship
directions: Gather all ingredients together and mix with a package of people (4th graders work best).
Work ingredients into package gradually.
Pour mixture onto a nice ballfield, blacktop or other structure and enjoy a fun game!

title: skillet salad
directions: Heat butter in skillet with cover.
Toss in vegetables and seasoning; mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 to 18 minutes or until cabbage is tender but crisp.

title: creamy skillet cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, combine cabbage and vinegar. Cook, covered, over medium heat 8 minutes or until cabbage is softened. Remove from heat.
Combine honey, mustard and yogurt.
Stir into warm cabbage.
Just before serving, sprinkle with paprika.
No fat and 73 calories.

title: pretzel surprise salad
directions: Combine butter, pretzels and 1/4 cup sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan, mixing and spreading over bottom.
Blend cream cheese, whipped topping and 1 1/2 cups sugar in bowl.
Spread over pretzel layer.
Drain the strawberries and pineapple reserving juices. Combine reserved juices with enough boiling water to measure 2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice mixture in bowl.
Stir in 2 cups ice and water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in fruit. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Garnish with pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: church street nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Add milk and flour combined with baking powder and salt, alternately.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: two-toned chocolate fudge
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Spread into aluminum foil lined 9-inch square pan.
In another saucepan over low heat, melt milk chocolate chips with remaining sweetened condensed milk, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread over fudge in pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board and cut into desired squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food chopper, grind apples and cranberries; mix with pineapple.
Add sugar; let set while mixing jello.
Mix the boiling water with jello; let set until cool (not firm).
Mix all ingredients together; let set until firm.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook together raisins and water until 1/2 water remains.
Cool and save water.
Drain raisins.
Mix and cream the shortening, sugars and egg.
Stir in cooled raisin water and vanilla. Sift together and stir in dry ingredients. Add applesauce.
Lastly add and stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Fry bacon and drain.
Add to hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream, then stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in the squash.
Combine stuffing mix with butter or oleo.

title: home ec yum yums
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pat into margarine. Layer remaining ingredients (except condensed milk) in order over crumb mixture.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix well in order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let stand at least 1 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Top with 1 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with white sauce seasoned with chicken broth or bouillon.
(Add a little curry, if desired.) Serves 12.
Freezes well.

title: buffalo chicken dip
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients, then add the cream cheese, and dressing. Put into a baking dish and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt the margarine with the stuffing mix.
Add half to the squash, carrots and onion.
Add sour cream and mushroom soup.
Put in buttered casserole with remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Heat margarine and Coke in a saucepan until it comes to a boil. Pour over flour-sugar mixture and
mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, cocoa, vanilla, baking soda and marshmallows; beat well. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: snowy apricot bars
directions: Place apricots in 2-quart saucepan; add enough water to cover. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes; drain.
Cool.
Chop and reserve.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into granulated sugar and 2 1/2 cups baking mix until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer 3 times the lettuce, onion and bacon with cauliflower on top of last layer.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and put on top but do not mix together.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours then mix together and serve.

title: apple and carrot casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam or other vegetable spray.
Place half of the apples and carrots in the dish.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Sprinkle flour mixture over the apples and carrots. Place remaining apples and carrots in dish.
Pour orange juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until apples are tender. Stir once during baking time.
Put lid on casserole.
Serve hot. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Peel pumpkin; cut into small pieces.
Put in a large saucepan. Add sliced onions, chopped potatoes, crumbled stock cube and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer uncovered 25 minutes, until soft.
Push through sieve or blender.
Return puree to saucepan.
Add cream, salt and pepper and reheat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite sized pieces.
Add brown gravy and cook 14 hours at 456°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but only if necessary.
This is because most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: strawberry delight salad(diabetic)
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Crush strawberries in blender or by hand. Add to gelatin mixture.
Add yogurt, vanilla and sugar substitute. Stir mixture until well blended.
Pour into four individual molds; chill until set.
Remove from molds and serve
on lettuce leaves.
Yield: 4 servings (each serving is 1/2 cup).
Exchange for 1 fruit.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix.
Add eggs and pumpkin; beat on high to break up pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted 2 times all at once, then add nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan (pan will be almost full; make cupcakes with leftovers).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cake will be moist but not sticky on inserted stick.

title: ocean spray holiday punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix cranberry juice cocktail, pink grapefruit juice cocktail and lemonade concentrate. Chill.
Just before serving, add club soda.
Makes 36 (6 ounce) servings.

title: grandma's corn
directions: Thaw corn.
Do not drain.
Put corn in a pan.
Add butter and cook until hot.
Add flour to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl: broccoli, onion, bacon, almonds and drained raisins.
Mix well.
In a smaller bowl, mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over mixture in large bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Cover top with basil leaves.
Then sprinkle oregano on top.
Allow to cook down 4 hours on simmer.

title: applesauce salad
directions: In saucepan, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice.
Heat until it begins to boil (bubbles).
Add applesauce and pour into dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
a Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits in half
(use	1
can	at
a time to avoid dough getting sticky). Coat
with	sugar
mixture.
Layer	in greased Bundt pan.
Pour butter mixture over coated biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let sit in pan for 5 minutes, then flip and serve.
May be made the night before and kept refrigerated.

title: baked beans
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly until lightly thickened and mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: bake-it-all mix
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
Sift into large bowl or pan.
Add shortening; use pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal and small peas.
Mix is ready to use or to store in a canister in a cool, dry area.
Use as you would use a commercially prepared biscuit mix.
Yields about 12 cups.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Line bottom of loaf pan with waxed paper. Grease paper and sides of pan. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Stir in chocolate chips, walnuts, dates and cherries until well coated with flour. In large bowl, beat eggs well; gradually beat in all sugar. Fold in flour mixture and pour into loaf pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until well done at 325°.
Cool in pan. Remove when cool and wrap in foil to store.

title: chris' favorite cookies
directions: Mix everything together, cereal last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Extra good if you add 1 cup chocolate chips or 1 cup raisins.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or large, heavy frying pan. When oil starts to smoke, add pork and stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes over high heat.
Remove meat and set aside on plate.

title: low calorie watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed on box.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Let set up and serve chilled. Calories: 110.

title: green papaya salad
directions: Peel and seed papaya.
Cut julienne.
Grind together garlic, red chilies and roasted peanuts with water.
Mix together the papaya, cherry tomatoes, fish sauce, lime juice and mint leaves. Add garlic mixture and toss lightly.
Place papaya mixture on an ample bed of lettuce for garnish and for eating.

title: red jello with applesauce
directions: Combine and pour in a mold.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours). Unmold and garnish.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Brown pork chops.
Butter a baking dish.
Layer potatoes and onions in a dish.
Place several pats of butter on top of potatoes and onions.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Place pork chops on top of all other ingredients and bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 350° and then covered for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pound cake loaf
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder and nutmeg if used.
Beat butter on medium speed about 30 seconds, until softened.
Gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Beat 6 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; finish cooling on wire rack.

title: *pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add nuts, syrup, sugar and flavoring.
Bake in unbaked crust for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until set.
Makes 1 very thick or 2 thin pies.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paprika.
Spread in baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles (about 15 to 20 minutes). Use crackers or chips for dipping.

title: rudolph's beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch, vinegar, oleo, juice and beets; cook.
Makes sauce.
Pour over beets and set for 30 minutes.

title: lillian's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 1 pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: After putting your cooked chicken in the baking dish, mix chicken broth and soup together and pour over chicken.
Next, put vegetables over soup mixture.
Mix flour, butter and milk and pour over.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until top is browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil with electric mixer.
Add pumpkin and flour mixture until well combined.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes, or until toothpick comes out dry.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and turn out of pan. Cool completely.
Serve, thinly sliced.
Makes 1 large loaf. (Three mini loaf pans may be used; test after 45 minutes.)

title: party chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add stuffing mix; mix well to coat.
Line 9 x 11-inch baking dish with 2/3 of stuffing mix.
Mix chicken, soups, milk and vegetables in bowl.
Pour over stuffing mix and top with remaining crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; brown 10 minutes.
Try different variations with vegetables to suit your family's tastes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients. Heat and serve.

title: peach-pineapple preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil hard for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 (3 ounce) boxes of peach jello.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine flour, rolled oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and margarine in bowl to form crumbs.
Press half of crumbs into bottom of 9-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts over baked crust.
Mix caramel topping and flour; drizzle over chocolate pieces and nuts. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over caramel topping.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Chill for easy cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken broth in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cut flour tortillas into strips and drop into broth one at a time. Stir gently.
Boil 10 minutes without a lid.
Put lid on pot and boil another 10 minutes.
Add chicken and heat through.

title: lynne's confetti rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Pour broth into a 2-quart baking dish.
Add rice and stir for 3 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables and cover dish.
Bake for 45 minutes and remove from oven.
Toss rice with parsley.
Based on 6 servings, each serving contains 350 calories, 18 grams fat, 665 milligrams sodium and 41 milligrams cholesterol.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in a pan and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Beat until blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: spicy taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble sausage
into medium skillet. Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain off any drippings.
Spread beans in ungreased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, then top with sausage.
Pour salsa over sausage; sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle olives and onions over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Spread with sour cream while hot and serve with chips.
Refrigerate leftovers; reheat in oven or microwave.

title: jen's sandwich bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir into yeast, honey, salt, eggs, oil and 2 cups whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add unbleached white flour until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on floured board 10 minutes or until elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Keep in warm place and let rise until doubled (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Punch down and divide the dough in halves. Shape into loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled (maybe 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Can be made all white bread by using all white flour or rye bread by substituting 2 cups rye flour for the whole wheat flour and adding 1/4 cup caraway seed.

title: martha's mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except Doritos chips and cheese.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, put layer of Doritos chips in bottom, then add layer of grated cheese.
Add layer of meat mixture, then repeat until all is used.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put into a gallon jar the cucumbers and onions.
Pack tightly. Bring all other ingredients to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cukes and onions.
Put lid on and keep in refrigerator.
Shake jar twice a day.
Refrigerate at all times.
Will be ready in a week.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix other ingredients, then
add
yeast.
Stir until well mixed.
Set aside in warm place
for
minutes.
Drop
into greased muffin pan. Bake
for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: jo ann turley's pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine. Press in bottom of baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: banana oat bread
directions: In bowl, cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with mashed bananas and milk.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to 1 inch on all sides. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 8 ounces of Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour over cooled crust.
Mix pudding, milk, pumpkin, cinnamon, allspice and salt until smooth.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone the chicken.
Melt the butter and pour over the stuffing; set aside.
Mix milk with soup.
Add chicken, peas, onions, almonds and pimentos.
Pour half of the stuffing in a 9 x 14-inch casserole and pour all the other ingredients over the stuffing. Place remaining stuffing over the top.
Casserole should be shallow. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mint fudge sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes).
Boil 3 minutes, remove from heat. Immediately add chocolate chips and beat with a wire whip until smooth.
Stir in crme de menthe or mint extract.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick lunch salad
directions: Chop lettuce and tomato.
Add drained, mixed vegetables (do not cook).
Add Frito corn chips, mayonnaise, pepper and salt to taste.
Add chopped eggs last.
Toss and eat.
Makes a large bowl full.

title: grandmother larson's tomato beef
directions: Cut round steak into very thin strips, 2 inches long.
Cook meat in large skillet on medium.
When meat is partially browned, add strips of green pepper, slices of onion.
Cook on medium high until vegetables are just starting to be limp.
Add sweet and sour; heat.
Turn off heat; add tomatoes and mix.
Serve with rice on the side.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat 1 quart of rich milk in double boiler.
When hot, add the well beaten yolks of 3 eggs, diluted with 1/2 cup cold milk.
Beat the whites to a stiff froth, adding a pinch of salt.
When well beaten, add 1 cup sugar and beat until smooth.
Add slowly the heated milk and cook until thick.

title: creole flounder
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Place fish in greased baking dish. Combine other ingredients and spoon over fish.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until flaky.
Garnish with tomato wedges and green pepper rings.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add stuffing mix and mix well.
Spread 3/4 stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of stuffing.
Lay pieces of mushrooms (drained) on next.

title: crescent quiche
directions: Separate dough into four triangles.
Place two in ungreased pan (8 or 9-inch).
Press on bottom and 1/2-inch up sides.
Seal seams.
Place cheese over dough.
Sprinkle with meat and onion. Blend celery salt, salt, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat.
Put remaining triangles over the meat and eggs mixture.
Do not seal. Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes or until filling is set and is a golden brown.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and paprika. Dip chicken pieces in beaten eggs and roll in flour mixture until well coated.

Place chicken in a greased baking dish and sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top. Dot with margarine and bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning once after 30 minutes. Be sure dish is large enough for chicken pieces to keep from touching.

title: carrot apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease 2 (9-inch) cake pans and line with waxed paper.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.
It is good with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pear relish
directions: Cook 30 minutes after it begins to boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in a 7 inch x 11 inch casserole dish.
Put cooked chicken on top. Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice, curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Combine stuffing crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over previous mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower or broccoli bake
directions: Cook vegetables.
Place in ungreased round casserole dish. Beat soup and milk together and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yum!

title: california orange chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Cut up chicken into serving pieces. Arrange chicken pieces in a baking dish with lid.
Add garlic and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and black pepper. Cover dish with lid.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour orange juice over chicken and add orange rind. Pour juice from pan over chicken.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Continue baking another 20 minutes until juices run when thigh flesh is pricked.
Garnish as desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together. Roll into balls. Don't grease pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients. Put in a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover with the melted butter, cornflakes and almonds. Heat (loosely covered with foil) at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil for the last few minutes and brown top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, mash bananas.
Add soft margarine and sugars.
Beat 1 minute.
Add all ingredients except nuts.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour in ungreased large loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour (350°).

title: angie's cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in chopper or food processor until smooth.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up the bread slices and put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain the sausage and then spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with the grated Cheddar cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in the baking dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and onion; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Remove when golden brown. Drain well.
Great with salsa.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in 1/2 stick of butter.
Beat egg and add buttermilk while stirring.
Add egg mixture into your mixed dry ingredients.
Roll out dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut circles for scones out of dough.
Bake approximately 7 minutes at 400°.

title: spicy nut triangles cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour mixture gradually, stirring well.
Spread dough evenly in 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Beat egg white and brush over top.
Smooth surface with fingertips.
Sprinkle nuts over dough and press in. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
While warm, cut into 4 length strips than 6 crosswise strips.
Cut each piece in half diagonally.
Makes 48.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Mix soups and milk, pour a little on bottom of pan to cover. (Hint:
spray pan with no-stick spray to start.)

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika over the ingredients and serve cold on a lettuce bed.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour cherry pie filling in 9 x 13 inch pan. Add can of crushed pineapple, with juice and mix together in pan so it is evenly distributed. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over fruit. Sprinkle with chunks of butter. Top with nuts. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until top is lightly browned. Serve hot or at room temperature with ice cream or whipped cream. When this is baking, your kitchen will smell wonderful!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish; cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in 2-quart bowl. Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted butter or margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in center of oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and add graham cracker crumbs to make a crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of margarine for 10 minutes.
Spread on top of crust. Next, slice bananas on top of the sugar mixture.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread thawed whipped topping over pineapple. Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.

title: pineapple-cherry squares
directions: Place half crumbs in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half coconut.
Cream butter gradually; add confectioners sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Spread over coconut.
Fold pineapple, cherries and nuts into whipped cream.
Spread over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with remaining coconut and crumbs.
Chill 4 hours.
Cut into squares.
Trim with pineapple and cherries.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes; let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine milk and butter in a 2-cup measure.
Microwave 1 minute on High to warm milk.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop out cooked potato into medium bowl.
Add milk and butter mixture.
Season with salt and pepper. Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Heat griddle; add butter to griddle.
Butter the bread.
Put 1 slice of bread, face-down on griddle.
Stack cheese slice and second slice of bread with butter face up.
Cook until lightly browned.
Turn; cook other side until lightly browned.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix
together
the
oats,
wheat bran, sunflower seeds, coconut, nuts,
sesame seed and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, mix honey, oil and water and heat in microwave until hot.
Add honey mixture
in
with the dry ingredients and mix very well. Spread on cookie
sheets
to make a thin layer.
Bake at 300° for 1/2
hour or until very lightly browned.
Add raisins and store
in
an airtight container.
Serve with slices bananas, peaches or yogurt.

title: hot punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bottom of coffee pot.
Put cloves and cinnamon in top of pot and perk 3 to 5 minutes.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place brisket in large baking pan.
Pour liquid smoke over meat; sprinkle with celery, garlic and onion salts.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Cut off fat, slice thin and return to drained baking dish.
Add barbecue sauce; bake for 1 hour.

title: low sodium cranberry fluff
directions: Grind the cranberries; mix with sugar and marshmallows and chill overnight.
Add the grapes, pecans, whipping cream and vanilla.
Makes 5 cups.
A 1/2-cup serving equals 32 mg. sodium.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onion.
In another bowl combine sugar, vinegar and the mayonnaise.
Pour over the broccoli mixture.
Toss to coat all; refrigerate.
Just before serving salad, sprinkle with bacon and sunflower seeds.
It's better as it sets and gets colder.

title: german meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, crumbs, 1/4 cup water, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Set aside.
In large skillet bring remaining water to a boil.
Add bouillon, sugar, raisins, lemon juice and gingersnaps.
Stir thoroughly.
Add meatballs to skillet.
Simmer until cooked, about 20 minutes. Serve with noodles.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or more coconut.

title: bits 'o brickle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the Eagle Brand milk, 1 egg, pecans and Brickle chips.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2 inch dish. In a sauce pan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening in flour; add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves side of bowl. Turn out dough on lightly floured board; knead until smooth. Roll dough out into a large (about 1/4 inch thick) rectangle. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples; sprinkle apples over dough. Roll up dough like a jelly roll. Slice dough in 16 slices; (1/2 inch thick) Place in melted butter. Pour sugar and water around rolls. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Chop onion well and add all ingredients together and mix well. Place in covered baking dish and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: country collard and turnip greens
directions: Note:
Must have seasoned black cast-iron pot.

title: summer salad
directions: Cook celery and carrots until you are able to pierce with a fork.
Cut all vegetables to bite-size.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over all vegetables.
Let stand one hour before serving.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: cranberry ring mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until thickens.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Serves 4 to 6.

title: famous corona salsa
directions: Combine jalapenos, garlic powder, salt, cilantro, pepper and onions in food processor and chop until onions are small pieces. Set aside in large bowl.
Drain water out of peeled tomatoes and chop in food processor until tomatoes are small and chunky.
Add chopped tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes and vinegar to onion mixture and mix by hand.
You may add a dash of hot sauce to spice it up or a pinch of sugar to sweeten it a bit.
Serve with tortilla chips or your favorite Mexican dish.
May be found in the produce department.
If not available, you may use dried cilantro from the spice aisle.
If food processor is not available, may be prepared by chopping by hand.

title: carrot cheddar casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in a lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 60 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water over medium heat.
Add onions, pepper and dill seed to bouillon mixture and cook several minutes. Add frozen cut green beans.
Cook, covered, 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange fluff jello
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients lightly.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, egg, buttermilk.
Add mashed bananas and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(I use 2 small loaf pans making 2 loafs; 1 large loaf pan for 1 loaf.)

title: jean's quick and easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix the package.
Mix according to directions with water and add to meat, then add all of your spices as listed.
Add in onions, potatoes and wine and let simmer, stirring occasionally.
This meal can be left to simmer until a late husband gets home.
Just before serving, add sour cream and mix well.
May be served plain or over rice or noodles.
Fix a fresh green salad and French bread and you have a quick meal.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit and add water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid; set drained fruit aside.
Bring juices and water to a boil and add to both packages of Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve well; add sherbet.
Mix until well blended.
Chill until slightly thickened; fold in fruit and spoon into a 6 cup mold.
Chill until set. Unmold on a platter.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer.
Makes enough for about 7 sandwiches. This can be left in a crock-pot after cooking to keep warm.
This is a great do-ahead for busy workers.
Make this on the weekend and heat in the crock-pot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers; melt margarine and mix with 1/2 of the cracker crumbs.
Press 1/2 of this mixture into bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Reserve some for the top of casserole.
Mix the soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Layer chicken on top of crumbs, then some soup mix, then some of the unbuttered crumbs.
Repeat, ending with soup mix.
Add the reserved buttered crackers to the top. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple pineapple celery salad
directions: Combine apples, pineapple and celery.
Combine juice, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until clear.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Stir in the walnuts.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the oil, sugar and eggs and beat well. Add the flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla to the oil mixture. Add the apples. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chilies or Ro-Tel.
Grate cheese and keep separate.
Layer in casserole the tortillas, chicken, onion, soups and Monterey cheese.

title: bite size cheesecakes
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Spray mini muffin pans with non-stick spray.
Sprinkle 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon of graham cracker crumbs in each mini muffin cup.
Shake mini muffin pan back and forth until crumbs are even.
Fill cups with mixture. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown around the edges of each mini cheesecake.
Cool for three to five minutes, then run a very small knife around the edges and then use a cookie sheet to flip the cheesecakes.
After completely cooled, top with sour cream and cherry pie filling.
Makes 6 dozen.
You can freeze ahead of time in an airtight container without the topping.

title: mimosa
directions: Mix and pour over crushed ice or use a blender.
Serve in deep wine goblets.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; add to beaten eggs.
Fold in zucchini.
Fry like pancakes in margarine.
(Serve these instead of potatoes.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all.
Add topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach in lukewarm water; drain, then chill.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and mustard.
Blend until thick and syrupy.
Tear spinach into bite-size portions and place in a bowl.
Add bacon and eggs; pour dressing over all and let stand.

title: schnitzbrod german christmas bread(makes 4 loaves)
directions: Optional:
