Candied fruits and peels, dried apricots, etc., may be added to suit individual tastes.

title: tchaikovsky's chocolate pudding
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Add the next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Let cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer in casserole until half full. Add a layer of sliced onions.
Add rice.
Add layer of browned, seasoned ground beef.
Add 1 can kidney beans.
Mix 1 can tomato soup with 1 can of water and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Add beans later in the cooking process.
Easy family favorite.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time, and beat. Add flour, soda, salt, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sour cream last.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until tested done.

title: pumpkin-yam dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon fruit biscuit crunchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip both sides of biscuits in melted margarine, then in sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With thumb, make deep indentation in center of each roll.
Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool.
Yields 10 rolls.

title: sara's hot tomato catsup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until all water is cooked out.
The mixture should be thick.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate malt drops
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs, well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: barbecue with sauce
directions: Cook on high in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.
Reduce temperature to low and cook for 8 hours.
(Keep about 3 inches water in pot while cooking.)
Turn off and let sit overnight.
In the morning drain and pick meat off the bone.
Add sauce to meat and cook in crock-pot on low for 3 hours.

title: topsy turvy tococorn bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread into 10-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: code breaker
directions: Mix together.
Roll the mixture into one-inch balls and place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Store the cookies in the refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together until thoroughly blended. Shape into small balls. Bake on cookie sheets at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ground casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and mix in onion.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: oma's applesauce
directions: Bring to a boil on high heat.
Turn down to simmer until apples are slightly mushy, but there are still chunks.
Delicious warm or cold!

title: pastor mason's waffles
directions: Beat eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, vanilla and sugar.
Mix well.
Makes 7 (4 section) waffles.
He always puts some buttermilk for milk which makes them lighter.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: white sauce for barbecue
directions: Use a quart jar.
Add all ingredients in jar and shake well. Use less vinegar to make thick and more vinegar to make thin.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken skin side up in a baking dish.
Blend together the rest of the ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
If too brown, put foil loosely over top.

title: gingerbread 2
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Batter will be very thin.
Bake in greased shallow pan 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated rump roast
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, sugar, ginger, crushed thyme leaves and garlic.
Pierce meat several times with a long tined fork. Place meat in plastic bag; set in deep bowl.
Pour marinade in bag and close.
Refrigerate overnight.
Occasionally, turn bag to distribute marinade.
Remove meat from bag.
Reserve marinade. Put meat on rack in shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for about 2 hours for medium done, basting with marinade during last 30 minutes.
Strain remaining marinade; heat with 2 tablespoons of water.
Spoon over meat slices.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mandarin rice salad
directions: In a tube pan, wipe with oil.
In bowl, mix rice, remaining oil, oranges and pineapple.
Mix coconut and juice form both fruits; set aside.
Layer rice mixture, then peas, then rice, then peas. Top with coconut liquid.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve on bed of endive or escarole with shaved purple cabbage to garnish.

title: tea-tang mixture
directions: Put all ingredients in	large tightly covered container and mix thoroughly.
Shake container
any time	you
make this tea. Add 3 teaspoons mix to each cup boiling water.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large non-aluminum pan. Bring to a boil, remove from heat. Ladle at once into hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes about 5 half pints.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and eggs. Add the milk and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Before baking sprinkle 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar over the cake.
Bake.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat eggs and milk.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Bring to boil water, onion, and chilies.
Boil it for 10 min. Add V-8, salt, garlic, picante sauce, and oil.
Boil for 10 more min.
Add shrimp.
Boil it for 10
- 15 min.

title: apple crisp(heavy, moist cake)
directions: Bake in greased 9 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: goblin good gorp
directions: Mix together.
Place in can.
Put in sandwich bags for treats.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple (juice and all) with dry Jell-O in a saucepan. Cook 5 minutes, turning down heat and covering when it comes to a boil. Chill. When cool, add buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip. Mix ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch container that's been sprayed with Pam. Refrigerate overnight.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Dice salt pork and render until crisp in large kettle.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Discard all but 3 tablespoons grease. Saute onion and celery in kettle until tender; add liquid, bouillon cubes, bay leaves and thyme.
Add carrots and potatoes; bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook until carrots are almost done.
Add cream-style corn and sugar and continue cooking until vegetables are very tender.
Add can of evaporated milk and season to taste.
Add more sugar, if needed, and salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top of chowder with crisp salt pork.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix together in large bowl the shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla; beat until soft.
Add sour cream; mix.
Add flour mixture; mix.
Roll out on lightly floured surface, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Ice and decorate as desired.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs, then add diced apples.
Sift together the flour, salt, spices and soda; add to apple mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and cinnamon. Set aside. Place a spoon of apple pie filling into crescent rolls and roll up. Place in casserole dish and spoon sugar mixture over rolls. Pour Mountain Dew over the top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve hot with Blue Bell on top.

title: brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir, do not beat.
Just be sure it is mixed up.
Pour in a square pan (greased and floured). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 pan.
Add cracker crumbs and spread evenly.
Layer rest of ingredients and pour Eagle Brand milk over top evenly.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves or	4
1/2 x 3 1/2-inch) loaves.

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Spoon batter into hot muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown bacon and chopped onions together.
Do not drain off fat.
Drain all beans, except the pork and beans.
Add all beans to the bacon, onions and fat.
Mix catsup, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add to beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 250° for 3 hours.
Beans may be frozen and reheated.
Serves 24 or more.

title: peanut butter cookies plus 2-year old
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Get 2-year old out of bathroom where she is wading in toilet in $40.00 orthopedic shoes.
Measure flour.
Unwind 2-year old from around right leg.
If unsuccessful, drag her across floor to answer phone. Wash flour off child, phone cord and right leg.
Mix the rest of ingredients and stir in.
Before putting dough in refrigerator to chill, clean up floor where dogs food was spilled, wash dog food out of child's teeth.
Turn on Gerbert video and tell child to watch for Daddy.
Turn oven to 375°.
Take coloring books and melted crayon out of oven.
Begin search for broiler pan.
Do not disturb turtles living in it.
Accept offer of 2-year old to use cake pan from Dolly-Time bake set, which bakes one cookie at a time the size of a tooth filling.
Wash 2-year olds hands and prepare to roll dough into balls the size of large walnuts.
Take 2-year old to bathroom to wash her hands again before placing the cookie on the pan.
Get dog off 2-year olds lap and wash her hands again. Flatten cookie with fork dipped in flour before putting in oven. Mop floor.
Hose down refrigerator, cabinets and stove.
Get flour off living room sofa.
Catch 2-year old who is chasing dog with portable mixer and contain her in bathtub.
Yield:
one cookie.

title: fresh broccoli mandarin salad
directions: Prepare dressing a day or two in advance if you want.

title: quick breadsticks
directions: In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing and grated Parmesan cheese.
Spread on split bun halves.
Cut each bun half lengthwise into 3 strips or sticks.
Place strips, mayonnaise side up, on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 breadsticks.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to oleo mixture and mix well. Roll into balls or drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bon-bons
directions: Using toothpicks, dip balls into mixture.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a gallon container, mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric until sugar is dissolved.
Then add cucumbers and onions.
Keep in refrigerator.
Can be packed in jars after 3 days and kept in refrigerator.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.	Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.	Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in molasses and milk, add dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Stir in raisins.	Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen muffins.
Batter can be stored in refrigerator for 3 weeks and used as desired.

title: pork chops with mushroom soup
directions: Brown chops on both sides in frying pan with small amount of hot fat.
Place chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle French-style green beans on top.
Combine soup with 1/2 to 1 can water.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on a floured board and cut with a donut cutter and put in hot oil or fat.

title: try it you'll like it broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli; put in casserole dish.
Mix in stewed tomatoes and pour eggs over this.
Spread soup over mixture and dot with butter.
Spread cheese over all and dash of oregano.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: company corn
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low for about two hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake in iron skillet or cornstick pan at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, mix flour, nuts and melted butter or margarine.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°; let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread this onto crust.
Prepare chocolate pudding mix with milk.
Pour on top of last layer.
Prepare vanilla pudding mix with milk; pour on top of chocolate pudding layer.
Cover this with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: western meat loaf(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together ground beef, salt, pepper, onions, bell peppers, eggs, crackers and tomato sauce.
Cook the mashed potatoes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook corn until hot.
Add margarine.
In a cup, put flour and milk and stir until smooth.
Add to corn and let it thicken.

title: frijoles a la charra
directions: Clean and rinse pinto and kidney beans. Best if beans can be soaked overnight or bring to a slow boil for 20 or 30 minutes. Drain water and rinse thoroughly under faucet.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Cover the neck, wing tips and giblets in a 3-quart saucepan with 2 quarts cold water.
Gently bring to a boil.

Lower temperature to a low simmer with the bubbles just breaking the surface. Remove any foam and grease as it floats to the surface. After the stock is simmering clear, add the celery, onions and several carrot ends. Continue to cook the stock for several hours. Add water if the volume gets too low.
Strain the vegetables and meat from the stock, saving the giblets and neck meat.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Combine spaghetti, oleo, cheese and eggs.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine sauce, oregano and browned beef and spread over spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bake additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: bagogi(meat marinade)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Measurements are for 2 to 3 pounds of meat.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Excellent for wild game.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: four day sauerbraten
directions: Place all ingredients except meat and gingersnaps in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour this marinade over the meat, placed in a glass container. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 days, turning meat once or twice a day.
Drain and dry meat. Brown in fat. Add marinade and simmer for 2 hours.

Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Blend in 2 tablespoons flour and brown. Add to meat and simmer 45 minutes longer. Add crushed gingersnaps and simmer 5 to 20 minutes until meat is fork-tender. Strain gravy and serve with meat.

title: daddy's famous party mix
directions: Melt butter; add spices and mix well. In separate extra-large bowl, mix Rice Chex, Corn Chex, pretzels, nuts and bagel chips. Stir in the butter mixture. Spread mixture on cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning mix after 30 minutes. Cool on paper bags.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag add all ingredients.
Close and shake until potatoes are coated.
Empty potatoes into pan.
Bake forty minutes, stirring once.

title: pecan toffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan over low heat.
Add sugar.
Cook until it bubbles; add water and syrup.
Cook to hard crack stage (290°); must use candy thermometer.
Add nuts and pour at once on buttered cookie sheet.
Cover with candy bars.
When melted, spread over candy.
Break into pieces.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, milk and corn in a large bowl.
Add the dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in the onion, cheese, pimiento and peppers.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a preheated 350° gas oven until firm and lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Yield:
12 large servings.

title: date cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let stand.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma szepe's goulash
directions: *To make it hot, mix 1 1/2 teaspoons cayenne pepper into a small 1 1/4-ounce tin of paprika.

title: chinese fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well. Add pecans & Coconut. Mix well. Add crushed vanilla Wafers. (Add a little milk if too thick.) In a tube pan, Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour, turn oven to 250 degrees and bake another hour.

title: grandma's noodles
directions: Roll real thin in 3 strips and cut with a knife.
Boil until done.

title: smothered okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash okra, cut and fry in 2 T oil until not sticky.
Do not use iron pot.
In another skillet add 1 T oil and 1 T flour.
Add chopped onions, bell pepper & celery.

title: pepper steak
directions: Coat steak strips with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Add liquid from tomatoes. Reserve tomatoes. Add water (more as mixture cooks). Add onion and garlic.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until moistened.
Mix on medium setting for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased (not Pam) Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor or grinder.
Mix with marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
The next day, add apples, walnuts, salt and grapes.
Fold in whipped cream. Cover and let chill several hours.
To serve, place a mound of salad on a leaf of lettuce; garnish with a cluster of grapes.

title: meatballs with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream of mushroom soup and water. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in flour.
Fry in oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cream of mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add oil and water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture.
Add pumpkin, nuts and raisins. Grease and flour four coffee cans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes before turning out.

title: frittered squash blossoms
directions: In a bowl, blend
together the flour, salt, pepper, tarragon and eggs. Add the beer gradually, beating until smooth.
Heat the oil until very hot. Dip each squash flower in the batter.
Drop into the hot oil and fry until puffy and golden.

title: wisconsin baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook ziti in lightly salted, boiling water.
Drain well.
While ziti cooks, saute onion in butter in pan until transparent.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: karen's chop suey
directions: Brown together the first 3 ingredients; cover with water and simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to a simmer. Make flour and water thickening and add to make a gravy.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix dry salad mix into cream cheese.
Let stand at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix in heavy 2-quart saucepan sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil. (Mixture will be bubbly all across top.) Boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips. Stir until completely melted.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Add 2 c. marshmallow cream.
pour into 9 x 12 buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Half of recipe makes an 8 x 8 pan of fudge.

title: fantastic potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes; melt butter and add with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add topping. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and let stand overnight.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick mix, eggs, margarine and vanilla in an electric blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding with the one cup milk.
Blend in half carton of Cool Whip and
1/4 cup pecans until blended.
Pour in pie shell. Spread other half of Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill 1 hour.

title: green onion-beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 package of beef.
Mold into desired shape.
Put remaining beef (diced) on outside.
Chill.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients, then mix next 2 ingredients together.
Dip chicken pieces in egg and milk mixture, then in dry ingredients.
Put on broiler pan, after all pieces of chicken are coated.
Pour melted margarine over chicken pieces. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish whole wheat bread
directions: Sift flour with all dry ingredients, make a well in center of the mixture and add the buttermilk.
Stir until well blended. Knead gently with a little flour for 1 or 2 minutes.
With back of knife, cut deep cross.
Bake at 400° for an hour until golden brown.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package and drain.
Chop vegetables up fine and mix	all
together.	Put
into
greased casserole dish.
Pour in soup
and mix with vegetables.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, eggs, peas, onion, green pepper and bacon in a 13 x 9-inch container.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread on top like frosting.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
This is yummy and can be made the day ahead.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat all
ingredients together. Add water and vinegar.
Bring to boil.

title: barbecued bread
directions: Slice bread in 1/2-inch slices.
Spread both sides of bread slices with butter.
Sprinkle slices with spice and cheese. Reassemble loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter affairs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening and 1/2 cup peanut butter until crumbly.
Add syrup and milk, stirring until blended. Shape dough into a 9 inch roll and wrap in wax paper; chill at least 8 hours.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs and lemon extract.
Add flour and baking powder, which have been sifted together with raisins and pecans mixed in flour.
Blend well with sugar, eggs, butter mixture.
Pour in well-greased tube pan and bake 2 hours at 275°.
Do not overbake; may be done before 2 hours.
Test with toothpick.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a very large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, raisins, nuts and spices.
Heat together the margarine and applesauce. When hot, add the soda.
Stir and pour over dry ingredients. Stir well.
Add preserves.
Blend in and bake in a large tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Let cool well before removing from pan.

title: yippee yogurt pops
directions: You will need 10 (3 ounce) cold drink cups and 10 wooden sticks.

title: curry chicken
directions: Pour water over chicken breasts and boil.
Simmer for about 10 minutes. Cool until chicken can be handled.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in slow oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, pat dry and remove stems.
In a large bowl, chop mushroom stems, add parsley, walnuts, seafood and crackers; mix well.
Pour melted butter into mixture and toss gently.
Stuff mushroom caps and place on cookie sheet.
Broil for 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve all packages jello.
Using a mixer, mix in mayonnaise, cottage cheese and milk.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into oblong dish.
Place in refrigerator until jelled.

title: carrot salad (marinated)
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Cool in refrigerator.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add carrots. Let stand in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off grease and add 1 package taco seasoning mix dry; mix with hamburger.
In a large bowl put your chopped lettuce, tomatoes, onion, green pepper and Cheddar cheese, then mix with hamburger mixture.
Add Thousand Island dressing and 1/2 of the crushed Doritos chips.
Just before serving add rest of crushed Doritos chips on top.

title: karithopita(walnut cake with zwieback)
directions: Beat egg yolks until light in color.
Add sugar, vanilla, whiskey, water, cinnamon, cloves, baking powder, nuts, zwieback, orange rind and lemon rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Test with a toothpick.
Cool and pour the following syrup over it.

title: crab mousse
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine soup, cream cheese and gelatin.
Stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Cover with foil.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve as salad or dessert.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: roquefort dressing for the crowd
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Roquefort, lemon juice and chicken bouillon together.
Add all spices to the cream mixture, then add to the sour cream mixture.
Mix as little as possible.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: danish syrupscaga(molasses cookie)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured board to 1/16 inch thick.
Cut with pastry wheel in diagonal lines 2 inches apart, crossing each other to make diamond shapes.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: broccoli and green pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In another bowl, beat eggs with the rest of the ingredients except peas and crackers.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add a thin layer of broccoli and peas, then a thin layer of sauce.
Keep doing this until finished.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: sweet potato custard(you may use butternut squash or pumpkin.)
directions: If fresh, boil until tender or if canned heat until hot.
Put potatoes in mixer; add butter, milk, sugar, eggs, and vanilla. You may add cinnamon and cloves if desired. Mix well and put in uncooked pie shell. Bake in oven at 375° until brown and set good.

title: houston restaurant's baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes until done; peel and chop into large chunks. Melt butter in large pan.
Over low heat, slowly stir in cheese and sour cream until melted and well combined.
Add potatoes, green onions, salt and pepper.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and refrigerate overnight.
On day of serving, heat soup until hot.
Pour into soup mugs and sprinkle bacon bits or crisply fried bacon (crumbled) on top.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning.
Layer ingredients as listed in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Serve with chips.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: With small sharp knife or vegetable peeler, remove peel (no white) from 2 lemons; cut in thin strips.
Set aside.
(You should have about 2 tablespoons.)
Squeeze juice from lemons to equal 2 cups lemon juice; set aside.

title: cheesy biscuit sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Melt butter or margarine in 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Combine flour, cheese and chili powder. Cut in shortening until resembles coarse meal.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Turn dough out on lightly floured surface.
Roll into 12 x 10-inch rectangle; cut into 1 x 5-inch strips.
Dip each strip in butter; bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Mix together the pretzel crumbs, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for just 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: peanut buttered pork
directions: Tie pork loins together at 1 1/2-inch intervals with fat sides out.
Balance roast on spit and secure with holding forks.
Insert meat thermometer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange medium coals at rear of fire box.
Knock off ash.
Place foil drip pan in front of coals and under roast.
Attach spit; turn on motor and lower hood.
Roast at 170°.

title: jefferson davis pies
directions: Coat a 9-inch pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Crush the crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix with the sugar, butter-flavored sprinkles and egg white until the crumbs are moist.
This crust will not be as moist as one made with melted butter or margarine. Press onto bottom and up sides of prepared pie pan.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie shell or 10 servings.

title: hominy stew
directions: In 3 qt. saucepan combine beef, the 4 cups water, onion, garlic and salt. Cover simmer 1 1/2 hours; add hominy, undrained tomatoes with chilies and cumin.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes more. Blend the 1/2 c. cold water into flour, add to beef mixture; cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Serve in bowls; top with shredded cabbage and green onions, if desired.
Makes 6 - 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Deep fry at 425° until golden brown.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook beef until lightly browned; drain.
Combine all ingredients in electric slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low setting 10 to 12 hours or on high setting 5 to 6 hours.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Boil ingredients and put in dish and cool completely.
Top with
8 ounces sour cream, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese. Bake until heated.

title: jam sticks
directions: Mix, leaving out jam.
If dough is hard to handle, chill about an hour. Divide dough into 12 equal parts.
Place on well-greased cookie sheets.
Shape into rectangles 8-inches long and 1-inch wide.
With wooded spoon, make a furrow down center of each piece of dough.
Spread jam in furrow.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets.
Cut into slices. When cool, frost.

title: white bread
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water, yeast and 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead 10 minutes, let rise 1/2 hour.
Punch down, raise another 1/2 hour.
Punch down and put in 3 loaf pans. Raise again.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: almond brittle
directions: Cook until sugar is melted and nutmeats begin to pop.
Keep cooking a while longer.
Pour on buttered platter.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: lime-light pie
directions: Crust:
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in Crisco and drip in melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with cold water.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "more"
directions: Boil egg noodles until tender; fry onion and garlic (chopped) in 2 tablespoons fat until tender.
Add ground meat and hot sausage; cook until well done.
To this add noodles, whole kernel corn, tomatoes, peas, salt and chili powder.
Put in 1 large oblong dish or 2 large baking dishes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large skillet saute onion in melted butter until tender. Then add soup and can of water.
Add thawed broccoli and salt. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Add Minute rice and mix all together. Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole, cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: dots salad
directions: Combine jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Drain pineapple; add cold water to juice to make 1 cup and add to jello.
Chill until partially set.
Soften cheese and whip together with mayonnaise. Add to jello and stir well.
Add other ingredients and chill until firm.

title: cheese-n-spinach puffs
directions: Mix cooked and drained spinach together in bowl with all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place toothpicks in each one and serve.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and pour in electric (or hand crank) ice cream freezer and run until it stops.
Can add 9 bananas, 1 cup chopped nuts or 3 (10-ounce) packages frozen strawberries.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: low sodium seasoning
directions: Thoroughly mix and store in airtight container.
Sprinkle over vegetables and meats.
Contains less than 1 calorie per teaspoon.

title: yummy fruit pie
directions: Mix together first ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Put onion slices in pan.
Place chicken on top of onion. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Simmer, covered, basting with the sauce.
Add water if it becomes too thick.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: lloyd's chili
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add undrained kidney beans, tomatoes and the remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour. Stir occasionally to prevent burning.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Chop up onions, green pepper, garlic and celery, quantity as desired.
Mix French's spaghetti mix according to directions on package.
Add ground beef, onions, green pepper, garlic and celery, which have been browned on top of stove.
Be sure and drain excess grease before adding to spaghetti mix.
Let the sauce simmer for a while.
At this point you can add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce and a little sugar to taste, if desired.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender. Remove from heat and add chicken, chili sauce, sour cream and salt.

title: pasta pronto
directions: Brown sausage, break up into small pieces as it browns. Remove from pan when cooked.
Put oil in pan.
Add onion and garlic powder.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper and saute 3 minutes.
Put sausage back into pan and add chicken broth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sausage mixture to hot cooked pasta, along with parsley, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in preheated oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Meanwhile, in 9-inch pie pan, combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, salt and garlic powder.
Dip fish fillets in butter and then in crumb mixture.
Arrange fish fillets in baking pan.
Bake near center of oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until fish is tender and flakes with fork.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with sugar until tender; drain and mash. Beat in egg.
Add butter; top with cheese.
Bake until it sets.

title: pineapple and coconut cake frosting
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Cook everything, except coconut and vanilla, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla.
This is very good on plain yellow or pineapple layers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal.
Form into rolls and chill thoroughly, then slice off and bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: *To make sour milk, add 1 tablespoon of vinegar to 1 cup milk and let stand 10 minutes.

title: flan de leche(spanish custard)
directions: Scald the milk with the salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs with 8 tablespoons of sugar and vanilla until light and foamy. Add scalded milk to egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Set aside.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Add pineapple to sugar; bring to boiling point.
Add gelatin; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add lemon and cherry juices to mixture.
Cool.
Mash cream cheese; add chopped cherries to cheese.
Put cream cheese mixture in the gelatin mixture, a little at a time.
Add red food coloring. Chill until slightly thick.
Add whipped cream.
Put in mold overnight.
Makes 1 quart.

title: skillet barbecue
directions: Use leftover chicken, pork, beef, lunchmeat (Treet or Spam) or 1 pound ground beef.
If using ground beef, brown with onions and pour off excess fat.
If using other meat, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in ketchup, water, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add meat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool completely.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk to pudding mix with cream cheese; beat until thick.
Spread over cake.
Spread pineapple over cake next, then spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: goo cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pat into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat for 3 to 5 minutes. Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put back into oven and let stay long enough for cheese to melt.

title: blender orange bread
directions: Trim a thin slice from both ends of orange; cut fruit in half, lengthwise with a shallow "v" shaped cut, remove white center core. Cut into chunks and place in blender with 1/4 cup orange juice. Cover and whirl on highest speed until pureed.
Add enough additional juice to yield 1 1/4 cup In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Thoroughly combine orange puree with sugar, eggs, and melted margarine.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until loaf tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before turning out on wire rack.
Can also be made into muffins.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spread bread evenly in bottom of well greased baking dish, 8 x 11-inch.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Arrange sausage on top.
Beat eggs well; add 2 1/4 cups of milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Mix together mustard and soup; add remaining 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix well; pour on top of casserole.
Cover tightly with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven; set oven to 300°.
Bake abut 1 1/2 hours or until puffy and brown.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Choose small potatoes and boil them in their skins.
Peel while hot.
Toss well in melted butter and season with salt and parsley.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cecile's stuff
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Unroll both cans of crescent rolls onto a foil-lined cookie sheet. Press seams of dough together to form a large rectangle. Set aside. Brown ground beef and onions in skillet: drain well. Stir barbecue sauce into ground beef to moisten and spoon mixture down center of crescent rolls. Top with your choice of cheese. Fold crescent rolls over meat mixture sealing top and ends. Bake for 15-20 minutes until golden.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate.
Sift flour and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown the beef. Stir in celery and onion. Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into lightly buttered baking pan and bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
It will be firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and layer into casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream together, pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top until casserole is covered.
Melt one stick of butter or margarine, pour over crackers.
Bake at 350` for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: In a 13 1/2 x 9-inch dish, cube 4 slices of bread on bottom of dish.
Mix chicken, onion, green pepper and celery with mayonnaise. Spread over bread cubes.
Put the remaining bread (crusts removed) on top of thicken mixture.
Mix eggs, milk and broth and pour over. Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; mix all ingredients together. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange mellow frost
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into mold.

title: lemon pecan fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well. Combine 2 cups flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Coat pecans, pineapple and cherries with 2 cups flour and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cover and let stand overnight.
The next day, put mixture into a greased tube pan and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.
Yields 6 pounds.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Mix egg yolks, Mazola oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Then add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add chopped nuts, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in two regular loaf pans, greased and floured, 1 hour at 325°.
Cool on rack.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Add rice.
Stir until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and broth.
Bake in oven at 350° until broth has evaporated, about 30 minutes.

title: honey pork oriental
directions: Cook pork in small amount of oil in skillet, stirring frequently, for 15 minutes.
Mix gravy mix, water, honey, soy sauce, vinegar, ginger and garlic salt together.
Pour over pork; cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 10 minutes more. Add onion and pepper and cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, bourbon, flour, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Stir well. Sprinkle chocolate chips over pie shell.
Pour filling over chips and arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer or until set. Serve with lightly sweetened whipped cream, if desired.

title: chocolate mousse masterpiece
directions: Bake cake per directions in 3 layer pans.
While still warm, pierce with fork and pour 1/2 cup Kahlua over layers.
Prepare chocolate mousse mix with milk per directions.
Layer in glass bowl:
chocolate cake, chocolate mousse, candy bars and Cool Whip (do this 3 times).
Chill approximately 4 hours (or until mousse sets).
Top with chocolate curls (Hershey bar peeled with peeler).

title: stuffed chicken breast(cordon bleu)
directions: Wash and skin chicken breasts; count two halves per person. Between waxed paper, pound chicken thin and dust with garlic salt. Place a slice of ham (optional) on top of chicken, on top of this, place an oblong slice of cheese.
Roll up and pin with toothpicks.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in corn flake crumbs. Refrigerate for at least an hour.
(These can be frozen for several days and thawed before cooking.)
Heat cooking oil until it sizzles when a drop of water is dropped in.
Brown chicken breasts quickly (3 minutes or less).
Place browned chicken breasts in casserole dish; place in 350° oven and cook for about 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: millionaires
directions: Remove chocolate caramels from package and save for another use.
Unwrap remaining caramels and place in 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes.
Stir well.
Add milk to caramels and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir mixture until smooth; add pecans, mixing well. Drop by teaspoonful onto buttered waxed paper.
Cool, cover and chill.
Combine chocolate chips and shortening in 4 cup glass measure.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Dip caramel centers into chocolate and return to waxed paper.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with crumbs.
Pat lightly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Mix eggs, rest of margarine, confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla in mixer for 10 to 15 minutes. Spread mixture over crumb crust.
Cover with sliced bananas. Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Mix 1 teaspoon vanilla with Cool Whip and spread over pineapple.
Top with chopped nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: loma saltado
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch slices.
Marinate with olive oil, salt, pepper, cumin, chili pepper and garlic for at least 1 hour.
Heat French fries according to package instructions.
Brown meat quickly in frying pan.
Add tomatoes and onion; simmer until onion is tender.
Toss in French fries just before serving.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork or bottom of a glass and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate at least one hour before cutting.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in large pot.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add broth and milk; stir to keep from lumping.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper, onion powder, chicken, mushrooms and vegetables.
Cook until heated.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with rectangles of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine batter, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixer. Combine in separate bowl the flour and all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour milk.
Fold in zucchini and chocolate chips.
Flour and grease sheet cake pan or tube pan. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients in pan until thick and clear. Add the jello.
Pour over strawberries in prebaked shell.
Chill.

title: haystacks
directions: Note:
Amounts may vary with individual preferences.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Start with cookie crumbs on bottom.
Layer with pudding.
Put cookie layer on top.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water until tender; cool and cube. Remove broth.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 pints liquid.
Saute onions and peppers in oil or oleo.
Cook vermicelli in broth; drain.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add the regular tomatoes, the Ro-Tel tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and sugar. Drain peas and mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in large casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: de pepe salad
directions: Heat juice and thicken with sugar, flour and beaten eggs.
Mix with macaroni; let set overnight.
Next day, fold in fruit, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; then drop in 1 egg at a time.
When all eggs are in, beat 10 minutes.
Beat in dry ingredients, which have been sifted together alternating with milk, ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a large tube pan (greased and floured) at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Start in a cold oven.
Freezes well.

title: shrimp in beer
directions: Wash fresh shrimp.
Put all ingredients in pot.
Bring to boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turns pink.
Do not overcook.
Drain. Peel and eat.

title: italian tossed salad
directions: Serve on chilled plates with Italian bread or crisp crackers on the side.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Mix flour, shortening, water and salt for crust.
Roll out half of it for bottom crust and place in pizza pan.
Mix berries, sugar and cornstarch.
Place in pan on bottom crust.
Roll out remainder of crust and place on top.
Seal crust by pressing a fork all around the edge.
Baste top crust with a little milk. Bake in 425° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: fruit shortcake
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredient except fruit all at once. Cover bottom of Pyrex baking dish with drained fruit; sprinkle with sugar (white or brown).
Drop batter or pour evenly over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix turkey, bread crumbs and garlic together.
Make into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet until brown at 375°.
Place balls into pan with hot Ragu.
Serve over pasta or alone.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground round and chopped onion.
Drain off grease. Combine all ingredients and boil (simmer) for about 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water.
Bring to a boil and let boil 3 minutes.
Let cool and add 1 pint strawberries that have been washed and cut up.
Pour into crust that has been cooked, and let sit in refrigerator until set.

title: taco dip salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and seasoning mix.
Spread on a plate.
Top with a layer each of tomatoes, black olives, green onion and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips or Tostitos.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix together and let rise for 2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put onion rings on top and brown.

title: spinach pie(spanakopita)
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Saute onions in some oil; do not brown.
Combine with drained spinach and dill weed.
Whip eggs; add cheese and salt.
Combine all except 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, adding spinach and onions last.
Place in thawed pie shells that you have rubbed a little oil over; do not prick. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Place on middle rack of oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm.
The pie does not puff up.
You can use half Wesson oil and half olive oil. More oil and dill weed can be added if desired for taste.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tin can raisin bread
directions: Omit baking soda and salt if you use self-rising flour.
Boil the raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Cream together the egg, sugar and butter.
Mix all together and then mix the raisins, water and creamed ingredients.
Mix in the sifted dry ingredients.
Put batter in 4 well-greased soup cans or 2 (1 pound) coffee cans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, coconut and sugar in bowl and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake cake mix in 2 layer pans as directed.
Let cool and cut layers in half so that you have 4 layers.
Put one layer on cake plate, cut side up, and drizzle with topping.
Continue each layer with topping.
The longer it sits, the better it gets!

title: cherry pie tarts
directions: Open cherry pie filling and fill each pie shell. Add a small amount of Cool Whip on top of each shell and serve.

title: chilled fruit soup(good for brunch or dessert; easy and indestructible)
directions: Bring fruit, cinnamon and water to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Remove fruit and puree.
Add sugar to water.
Boil and dissolve.
Add lemon juice. Remove from heat. Stir in pureed fruit and chill (either in one bowl or individual servings). Serve with whipped cream and/or nuts (optional).

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple in a medium or large pan until just bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
(May also add chopped nuts.)

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a bowl.
Press 1/2 this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 6 minutes.
While this mixture bakes, melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
After bottom layer has baked 6 minutes, remove from oven, sprinkle with chips and spread caramels over it.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over the top; bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.
You can cool in refrigerator for 1/2 hour to let caramel harden before cutting.

title: ritz cracker snack
directions: Stir crackers and peanuts together in large baking dish.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, mix butter, sugar, and corn syrup.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes. Pour over cracker mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients set.
Beat the remaining ingredients together and add to the mixture after it is set. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Break bacon into small pieces.
Mix corn meal, soda and salt. Add milk, eggs and bacon drippings.
Mix well, then add creamed corn, grated cheese, bacon, onion, garlic and peppers.
Bake in hot, greased iron skillet at 325° for about 1 hour or until firm and brown.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Coat large roasting pan with Pam. Place popped corn in pan. In a heavy pan, melt butter.

Add sugar, syrup and salt. Bring to boil, stirring, then let boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat; add baking soda and vanilla. Pour over corn; mix well, then bake in 250° oven and stir every 15 minutes. Cook for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding(serves 1)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Ready to serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Combine yeast and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Shape into rolls or biscuits.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream dill weed, cream cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder together.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Spread vegetables on top.
Serve chilled.

title: mom's cure-all soup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: turkey melt with potatoes, peppers and onions
directions: Cut unpeeled, washed potatoes into 1 1/2-inch pieces, put in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Drain.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, vegetable oil, eggs and orange juice for 2-3 minutes.
Pour in 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Mix confection sugar and lime juice.
While layers are warm, pour over layers as a glaze.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar gradually.
Add lemon juice and strawberries.
Beat all this at high speed until well mixed and fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumb mixture in Pyrex dish.
Spoon strawberry mixture over crumb mixture and then top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze and then enjoy.

title: my homemade chili
directions: Mix together ground beef and tomato sauce.
Work thoroughly with hands.
Chop onion, pepper and garlic.
Stir all this together in large chili pot and brown over medium heat.
Add tomatoes and puree.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all together well; roll into egg-size balls.
Line pan with foil.
Make a tent with foil on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and black pepper.
Stir in green beans and half of the onions.
Add toasted almonds slivers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir; top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 8 1/2 cups, or 10 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion until done. Drain well and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Add other ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° until rice is done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Slowly blend in flour.
Cover dough.
Chill for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350° or 400°.
Roll out dough and cut cookies.
Place cookies on ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff; add sugar and beat until very stiff.
Chop nuts.
Mix with flour and add to egg whites after adding vanilla.
Drop by spoon onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat!
Leave overnight until completely cold.
Do not open oven door for any reason!
Chopped dates, coconut or chocolate chips may be added with nuts.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen cookies, depending on size.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute oleo, onions and celery.
Brown sausage and separate with fork.
Break up cornbread.
Mix all together.
Add eggs, cut up.
Salt and pepper to taste and sage, if desired.
Add juice from turkey giblets to moisten.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chili chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Tear tortillas into bite size pieces.
Then combine all and mix thoroughly.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
(Much better if left overnight in refrigerator before cooking.)
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain water off.
Add margarine, sugar, eggs, and milk.
Beat until there are no lumps.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. You can put coconut on top of the pies the last 15 mins. of cooking and let brown.

title: strawberry-banana jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice to dissolved Jell-O.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple to Jell-O.
Put 1/2 of the mixture into a mold or dish and allow to harden.
Spread sour cream over the congealed Jell-O.
Chill.
Add the remainder of the Jell-O slowly over the sour cream.
Chill to set.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix above ingredients and form into meatballs.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Core the middle of each of the squash, saving the insides and placing in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stuff each shell full; then make balls if you have extra place in pot. Pour tomato sauce over (and more seasons if desired).
Cook, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl; beat about 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Combine flour, soda, salt and apple pie spice; gradually add to sugar mixture, beating at low speed of electric mixer until blended. Stir apples and pecans into batter.
(Resembles cookie dough.) Spoon batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center and comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water. Add juice from blueberries and pineapple. Chill until it begins to thicken. Add fruits and nuts. Chill until set. Whip cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Spread on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: baked fudge(this is helen cheffy's recipe-it is easy, quick and delicious!)
directions: Mix all together.
Put into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over and bake at 350°
for one hour.
Blueberries and apple are my favorites.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: spaghetti sauce(plan ahead: uses slow cooker)
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is done. Transfer to a slow cooker. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, brown sugar, garlic, basil, oregano, salt and thyme. Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until heated through. Serve over spaghetti.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Combine the olive oil and butter in a saucepan.
Chop parsley and garlic and add to pan.
Cook on low for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain tomatoes (chopping the solid ones); add with the oregano.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan,
stir in flour until smooth, slowly stir in chicken broth & simmer 2 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add to other ingredients.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant; coat slices in salt and allow to sit for 30 minutes.
In saucepan heat Prego sauce, adding additional chopped onion and garlic (salt and pepper to taste).
Allow to simmer while preparing eggplant.
Rinse salt off eggplant slices. Dip each slice in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in olive oil until lightly brown.

title: zesty zucchini lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan brown ground beef until no longer pink; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce spices and seasonings, tomato paste, water, butter, basil and thyme. Bring to a boil, then simmer uncovered 10 minutes. In small bowl, combine ricotta cheese with egg; set aside. In medium saucepan, bring 1 quart water to a boil. Add zucchini and cook 2 minutes; remove and rinse under cold water. In 12 x 8 inch casserole, layer half the zucchini, ricotta mixture and meat sauce. Repeat layers. Top with mozzarella cheese and bake uncovered 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add and mix well 2 eggs (1 at a time).
Add walnuts and lemon rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Blend well the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg; mix until well blended.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and cloves.
Blend alternately with the applesauce into the sugar-shortening-egg mixture.
Add the vanilla, raisins and nuts; mix well.
The batter will be thin.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream
sugar,
eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, cream
of tartar and nuts.	Work until soft dough.	Chill 3 hours. Work
in
enough
flour
to roll out.
Cut in desired shapes or roll
dough
in
small
balls
and	press out with a floured fork onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until done.

title: beef noodle and corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and the next 4 ingredients in skillet until the beef is crumbly and the veggies are tender; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup and corn, stirring well.
Add cooked noodles and 1 cup of the cheese mixing well.
Then sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted, for 15 or 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Season chicken breast with Nature's Seasons.
Cut into strips. Saute strips in small amount of vegetable oil.
Then add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta of your choice.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Cook in saucepan over low heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Take off heat and add 3 cups oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lunch muffins
directions: Set toasted muffins aside.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a bowl.
Stir lightly.
Top each muffin half with mixture.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: lemon yogurt poppy seed pound cake
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, until color is gone.
Mix in flour and lemon yogurt (begin and end with flour). Add lemon extract.
Fold in poppy seed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes before removing to cake rack.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Add tomatoes to cooked beans.
Brown hamburger and onion; add chili powder and salt.
Cook until hamburger is brown.
Add to beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Mix all other ingredients with margarine until well mixed.
Chili powder may be added. Refrigerate unused sauce.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: the cake that doesn't last!
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix a well in the center.
Add eggs, pineapple, nuts, oil, vanilla and bananas. Stir; do not beat.
Will only take a few stirs to mix.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: congo squares
directions: Use large saucepan.
Melt shortening; add brown sugar.
When cool, add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
If mixture is too stiff to stir, add 1/4 cup milk.
Add nut meats, chips and vanilla. The mixture will be fairly stiff.
Spread on greased cookie sheet or in pan (10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 3/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: chili con queso(cheese spread)
directions: Fry bacon; discard all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add the remaining ingredients, stirring over low heat, until all is melted and blended.
Serve hot or cold as a spread with crackers.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: suisse mocha cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in sour cream.
Measure 1/4 cup of the mixture; set remainder aside.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cook and put in baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: crazy quilt bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg, milk and Bisquick in bowl; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Batter will be lumpy.
Stir in fruits and nuts; pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Fold into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with pecan half. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar and Karo syrup.
Heat in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts, butter and salt.
Heat in microwave on High for 5 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour onto pan sprayed with Pam.
Spread with spatula sprayed with Pam.
Cool and crack.

title: hot sauce
directions: If ripe tomatoes are used, peel and then chop.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except peppers, in order named in a large kettle.
Simmer uncovered until thick.
Add jalapeno peppers the last 15 minutes so they will stay hot.
Pour at once into clean hot jars and adjust covers as jar manufacturer directs.
If they don't seal, turn them upside down in the saucepan with a little water and boil about 6 or 7 minutes.
Enjoy this sauce with chips, tacos or any other food you want to spice up.

title: jeweled fruitcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add fruit, beaten eggs and vanilla. Grease loaf pans.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour or more, according to size of pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill.

title: pearl onion compote
directions: Saute onions in butter for 15 minutes or until caramelized. Add raisins and nuts.
Stir-fry for 2 more minutes.
Turn up high and add brandy and wine; 2 to 3 more minutes of stir-fry.
Add steamed carrots long enough to absorb other flavors.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Pour cold water in bowl.
Sprinkle gelatine on top of water. Place bowl over boiling water and stir until gelatine is dissolved. Cool.
Add mayonnaise, fish, celery, olives, salt, vinegar, paprika and dash of cayenne (if desired).
Turn into mold or molds that have been rinsed in cold water and chill.

title: hillary's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix in large container and serve.
May freeze and then thaw as desired.

title: pinto beans casserole
directions: Gradually pour cornmeal into boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Combine pinto beans with onions, olives, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Spread cornmeal on top. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese pork
directions: Mix salt, sugar, m.s.g., and tenderizer together.
Place in Tupperware container long enough to let the pork lie straight. Roll the meat in the dry sugar combination to coat.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
The meat will cause the dry sugar to create a syrup.
Turn the meat 2 or 3 times a day for 2 or 3 days to marinate.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli crescents
directions: Combine broccoli, Velveeta cubes, bread crumbs and bacon in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted.
Unroll dough.
Separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise, forming 32 triangles. Spread each triangle with cheese mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in oats and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: taco dip
directions: Microwave all ingredients together, except sour cream, until hot. Mix in sour cream.
Top with a few sprinkles of cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Melt bits and peanut butter in double boiler.
Add cornflakes and stir.
Add nuts and coconut.

title: prairie chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken, broth, vegetables and seasonings in large pot.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Cut cheese into chunks and add to soup, stirring until melted.

title: ham-it-up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles. Spread with mustard; sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seeds.
Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 pieces.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash with onion, sliced until tender.
Drain and mash coarsely.
Add margarine, salt, pepper and milk.
Stir in slightly beaten eggs.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with oregano and thyme.
Spread on bottom of a 9-inch pie pan. Top with 1 cup cheese and pizza sauce.
Sprinkle peppers over top. Top with additional 3/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with breadsticks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° until golden, approximately 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Enjoy!!

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemonade, lemons and milk. Fold together with Cool Whip and pour into pie shell; freeze. Good served with fresh peaches, strawberries, etc., or sprinkle with a few crumbled graham or cookie crumbs.

title: hot crab canape
directions: Pick crab meat carefully and shred it fine. Mix with enough mayonnaise to hold together. Season with Worcestershire sauce and Mexican pepper.
Peel cucumber and chop it fine.

Season lightly with salt and pepper. Spread a thin layer of cucumber on each bread round. Cover with a mound of crab meat, well smoothed. Place under the broiler to brown lightly. Decorate with parsley sprigs before serving. Makes 24 canapes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and set aside.
Brown sausage, onion and pepper in large skillet; drain grease.
Add soups, milk and macaroni.
Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Before removing from oven, add slices of cheese to top to melt.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion; drain. Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix top ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Cut apples up; measure in casserole dish.
Take apples out; spray dish with Pam. Put apples back in dish.
Mix mixture in with apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: dill pickles
directions: Make solution of water, salt, vinegar and pepper; heat to boiling point.
Fill crock with cukes, placing dill between layers.
Add hot solution.
A slice of onion or garlic may be added to boiling liquid if desired.
Cover crock and let stand several days before using.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place in greased baking dish the sliced apples.
Next mix together until crumbly the sugar, baking powder, salt, flour and egg; put over apples.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and pour over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: orange cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, blend egg, orange peel, juice and oil; stir into flour mixture until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Makes 12.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain juice from fruits except mandarin oranges.
Add enough water to make 3 cups; heat.
Add pudding mixes and stir until thick; cool.
Add bananas and drained canned oranges.
Stir in fruit.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix together the ground beef and rice.
Stir in the salt, black pepper, celery salt, green pepper, grated onion and garlic.
Form into 18 small meat balls.
Pour the tomato juice into a large skillet.
Add the cloves, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Mix well.
Add the meat balls.

Cover and simmer over a low heat 1 hour or until the rice in the center of the meat balls is tender. Occasionally remove the lid and turn the meat balls over if they are not completely covered with the tomato juice.
Add more tomato juice to make more sauce, if desired.
Some of the rice will cook into the tomato juice and thicken the sauce.
Serve on a hot platter.
Yields six to eight servings.

title: rice and water chestnut casserole
directions: In frying pan, brown noodles in margarine until golden brown. Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 inch pan and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: summer refresher
directions: Bring sugar and 7 cups water to a boil in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Bring remaining 2 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Add tea bags.
Cool; remove tea bags. Combine sugar syrup, tea mixture, lemonade concentrate and orange juice concentrate in large freezer container; mix well.
Freeze for 24 hours, stirring several times.
Store in freezer.
Fill glasses half full with slush.
Add ginger ale and mix gently.

title: sauce tropicale
directions: Combine the mango puree, sugar and orange juice in heavy saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and continue cooking until thickened, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Key Lime juice and extracts.
Serve over ice cream.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Melt remaining margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add bouillon cube and sauteed vegetables.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumb and cheese.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and congeal.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Cut into squares.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Put all ingredients into pan (except cheese) and cook until tender.
Now sprinkle cheese over the top and cook, covered, for 5 minutes so that cheese melts.
Serve over pasta.
Excellent!

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Mix well and set aside. Combine eggs, sugar and milk; beat well.
Add bread crumb mixture and pineapple, stirring well.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in oleo until tender (approximately 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings.

title: fruit and nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine orange, apple and pear slices. In a small bowl, combine oil, vinegar and honey. Blend well. Pour over fruit and toss to coat. Arrange fruit mixture on 6 lettuce lined salad plates. Sprinkle each with heaping tablespoonful of almonds.

title: millionaire pie(club member: neil h.)
