directions: Mix and pour into crusts; place in refrigerator.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix the first five ingredients together. Then pour and mix with cabbage and carrot.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: baked hash brown supreme
directions: Mix all together and put into greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients except for the dressing and chips. Add the last 2 ingredients just before serving.

title: death by chocolate(i made this for pra meetings; it is good enough to die for)
directions: Bake brownies and let cool.
Put fork holes in them and pour liquor over the top.
Make pudding according to the package directions.
Starting with pudding, alternate pudding, brownies, candy bars and Cool Whip in layers in large bowl.
Top with Cool Whip and some of the crushed candy bars.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Brush chicken pieces with butter.
Roll in cracker crumbs. Arrange pieces in a flat microwave baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High 12 to 15 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn halfway through microwaving time.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave easy opera fudge
directions: In 2-quart glass bowl, micro-melt the butter about 1 minute. Stir in dry mix and milk.
Cook, uncovered, until boiling, about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring every 15 seconds.
Add vanilla.
Beat in sugar; stir in nuts or cherries.
Pour into buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with nut halves, if desired.
Chill; cut in squares and store in refrigerator.

title: guatemalan chicken and rice(arroz con pollo chapina)
directions: In a large skillet brown the chicken in the oil over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. black pepper over chicken.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
In the same skillet fry the onion, garlic and tomato for 2-3 minutes.
Add the carrots, olives and capers and mix well. pour in chicken broth and add cooked chicken back into skillet.
Bring to a boil, cover skillet and reduce heat.
Cook until broth has been absorbed, about 10-15 minutes.
Add peas.
Heat oven to 300F.
Cook rice.
Place chicken in baking dish and cover with foil, poke 6-8 holes in top of foil to allow the steam to escape.
Bake for 30 minutes, spoon mixture over chicken one time during baking.
Garnish with red pimento slices, egg slices and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with rice, salsa and vegetables.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add mashed bananas to first mixture then flour and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: venison soup
directions: In a Dutch oven,
add
meat,
onion and enough water to cover. Simmer until meat
is
tender
and starts falling from the
bone. Remove meat and let cool;
remove from bone.
Chop or
shred meat.
While you are removing meat from bone, bring water
to
a boil and add all but the potatoes.
Simmer 1 hour or
until almost tender.
Add meat and potatoes; simmer until potatoes
are tender.
You may remove the onion or chop it up after the meat is tender.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Bring rhubarb to boil with sugar on low heat.
When it starts to boil hard, boil 5 minutes.
Add jello.
Stir until jello dissolves.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Set aside to cool.
In a bowl, combine Bisquick, cheese, milk and sausage.
Mix together thoroughly. Make into balls or spoon drop onto ungreased pan.
Cook in oven 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: way too easy zucchini pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients together. Place in a 9-inch baking dish, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered, then 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken broccoli stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir soup until smooth; add milk, stuffing, chicken, broccoli, stuffing and celery.
Mix well. Spread into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in large casserole dish.
Put sausage on top. Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt; pour over cheese.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: riverfront buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, melted butter and lemon extract until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Then add buttermilk and mix until creamy.
Pour into deep 9-inch unbaked pastry shell. Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 450° (until set).
Reduce heat and finish baking at 300° until knife comes clean when tested (about 45 minutes).
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: crunchy sweet pickles
directions: Cut cukes and soak in lime water (enough to cover) for 24 hours.
Rinse well in clear water.
Drain well.

title: five hour no peek stew casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a deep casserole dish and bake for 5 hours at 250°.

title: peanut butter fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well. Cover; chill thoroughly.
Serve dip with assortment of fresh fruit.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix and keep in tightly closed container.
Add 1/2 c. to 1 c. milk or buttermilk.
Pat out and cut out then bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix water with soup.
Cook until onion is done.
Then add other ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with seasoned stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pat bittinger's applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add applesauce and Karo syrup to butter-sugar mixture.
Dredge nuts and raisins with a little flour. Add flour mixture to butter-sugar. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Do not open oven door during the first hour.
Cake will double in size during baking and turn very dark.
Let cake cool in pan.
Invert when cool.
Cake tastes better 2 or 3 days after baking.

title: chicken wings in beer
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and margarine.
Pour over chicken and let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain chicken and save marinade.
In large skillet, brown chicken in margarine. Add browned chicken to marinade.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding over fruit.
Mix until thick.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: party bake pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Season well on both sides with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in lightly greased hot skillet.
Top each chop with onion slice and 1 tablespoon rice; cover with whole tomatoes.
Add any remaining tomatoes and juice to skillet.
Cover tightly; simmer over low heat or bake in foil-covered baking dish in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: Brown beef and pork in small amount of oil.
Add chopped white onions, celery and bell pepper in meat and cook 20 to 30 minutes, adding a little chicken stock to keep from sticking.
Add rice, giblets, seasonings, ground onions and parsley.
Cook a few minutes more to mix well.
Add enough chicken stock to make mixture moist.
Put into baking pan or casserole dish and bake uncovered about 45 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.

Dip chicken in butter, then in cracker mixture. Use shallow baking dish. Pour remaining butter over chicken. Do not turn. Lay foil over dish. Take foil off dish 15 minutes before time for browning. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "quick" shrimp dip
directions: In bowl mash shrimp.
Add and blend all ingredients together.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together and beat until light and fluffy 1/2 cup of shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add 2 well-beaten eggs, 2 tablespoons cream, vanilla or almond and beat well.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 8 minutes, or until delicately brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix potatoes and other ingredients in electric mixer.
Bake in casserole dish for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Put marshmallows on top and let melt.
Do not cook.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Depending on how much you want to make, you can vary the amounts of each.

title: apple pie(diabetic)
directions: The unbaked pastry may be used as a lower crust to hold the apple or as a crust to cover them.
If it is used as a lower crust, aluminum foil may be used to cover the open pie while baking so that the juice will be retained.
Place sliced apples in pie tin lined with pastry or in a greased pie tin.
Blend together flour, cinnamon and salt mixture with melted margarine.
Add sweetener and lemon juice.
Spread over apples.
Cover with aluminum foil or pastry.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with salt. Mix sugar, flour and butter until crumbly and spread over the apples.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve with topping.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and garnish, if desired, with whipped topping.

title: key lime shooter
directions: Mix this in order.
Shake and serve in a shot glass or miniature cordial.

title: hot pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients (except dressing) in a bowl and toss with dressing to moisten.
Serve warm.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Whip eggs and add sugar, salt, vanilla, corn syrup, butter and pecans.
Mix well and pour into pie shell. Bake on bottom rack for 1 hour.

title: southern cornmeal butter wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl with an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla and stir in 1 1/4 cups of the cornmeal and the flour. Mix well.
Place the remaining 1/4 cup cornmeal in a small bowl or plastic bag.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; coat with cornmeal and place on ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
With the floured bottom of a glass, flatten balls to 1/4-inch thickness; top each with almonds.
Bake until cookies are pale gold around the edges, about 8 minutes.
Cool on sheets for 1 minute before removing to wire racks.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in blueberries.
Sprinkle top with Crumb Mixture.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix
first three ingredients and put in 9x13 pyrex pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°, then let cool.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: chicken-rice supreme
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in a large bowl. Fold in rest of ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with crushed corn flakes. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Mix and marinate at least 3 days.

title: end of the garden pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, spices and salt in a large sauce pot. Bring to a boil then add prepared vegetables. Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Pack hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch space. Remove air bubbles. Adjust caps. Process for 15 minutes in a boiling water bath. Makes 5 pints.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Set the oven at 350°.
Line a 7 x 7 x 2-inch pan with heavy wax paper cut to fit.
Butter the paper.
Melt the butter and add all the other ingredients to it.
Stir well.
Spread in pan. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut in strips or squares while still warm. Let cool and lift out of pan.
Peel off any bits of paper that stick to brownies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute ground meat in a little margarine.
Drain well.
Saute peppers and onions.
Mix with ground meat.
Mix soups together. Add Worcestershire sauce.

title: diabetic angel food cake supreme
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Make vanilla (diet) pudding according to recipe.
Layer in a cake pan with sliced bananas and strawberries.
Top with topping and garnish with strawberries or sprinkle diet jello on top.
Makes 12 servings.
Calories 219, fat 6.2 grams and fat 25%.
Exchanges 2 starches and 1 fruit.

title: jordi's jello
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Pour into Dixie cups until 2/3 full.
Refrigerate.
When partially chilled, mix a few gummy bears or fish in each cup if desired.
When chilled, gently tear cup away and set broad base down or if not using gummies, may slice into rounds and arrange for a treat.

title: little upside-down cake
directions: Make yellow cake mix according to directions, but instead of water use 1 tablespoon pineapple juice.
In a bowl, mix butter, brown sugar and pineapple and put a little in each muffin pan. Pour the cake mixture batter over pineapple mixture, no more than 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Invert at once. Makes 24 muffin cups.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crackers, egg, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.

title: italian dinner rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of flour, yeast and Italian seasoning.
Heat milk, water, butter, sugar and garlic salt just until warm.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat in eggs.
Beat at low speed 1 to 2 minutes. Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in grated Parmesan cheese. Gradually beat in an additional 3 to 3 1/2 cups flour.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead in any additional flour needed to make a firm dough.
Knead until dough is smooth and can be formed into a ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (approximately 45 minutes).
Punch dough down; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 16 balls.
Brush tops of balls with a little melted butter and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Place rolls in two greased 8 or 9-inch round baking pans. Cover and let rise until about doubled, 15 minutes or so.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken with green peppercorns and mushrooms
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add mushrooms and saute until slightly browned.
Remove to a dish.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and pepper.
Dust lightly with flour.
Add rest of butter to pan mushrooms were cooked in.
When melted, add chicken and saute over medium to high heat until chicken feels springy to touch.
Remove to mushroom dish and keep warm.
Add white wine to pan; cook for a few seconds over high heat.
Add lemon juice, garlic and peppercorns.
Dissolve the bouillon cube in the hot water; add to the sauce and cook briefly.
Return chicken and mushrooms to the sauce and heat through.
Serve at once. (Additional salt and pepper may be added to sauce.
Also, if sauce is too thin, cream together 1 tablespoon each flour and butter and add to sauce to dissolve and thicken before adding chicken and mushrooms.)
Serves 4.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine, shortening, salt and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Add egg and mix.
Slowly add the flour, mixing long enough to combine (overmixing will cause cookies to spread when baking).
You may have to mix some of the flour in by hand.
Divide dough into parts about the size of a baseball.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate until dough is chilled. Using your hands, form each part into a long roll, about 1 inch in diameter.
If dough is crumbly to work with, keep mashing it together with your hands.
Refrigerate wrapped dough again until cold.
When ready to make, remove a roll from the refrigerator and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place cut side up on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb in center of each cookie to make indentation.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes, just until edges begin to slightly turn golden.
The cookies are prettier when white, so don't let them brown.
Cool completely on the sheet, then dab a small bit of frosting into each indentation.

title: lentil-hamburger soup
directions: Crumble ground beef into 3-quart casserole; add carrot, onion and garlic.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) for 4 minutes; break up and stir.
Cover and microwave until little pink remains in beef, 3 to 4 minutes longer; drain.
Stir in 2 cups hot water, stewed tomatoes (with liquid), mushrooms (with liquid) and remaining ingredients, except 1 cup hot water.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%), stirring every 6 minutes, until vegetables are tender, 24 to 28 minutes.

title: grandma farnen's homemade ketchup
directions: Core and quarter the tomatoes. Cook until soft. Put in sack to drain (pillowcase is fine) and hang for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Put through sieve. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 8 minutes and put in bottles.
(Old ketchup bottles are great; they will still seal.)
Thicken with cornstarch if too thin.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Wash, stem and dry berries.
Refrigerate in bowl with sugar until ready to serve, adding sour cream, ice cream and Cointreau at that time.
Ice cream must be slightly soft so that berries can be stirred into the mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five-grain bread(5 loaves)
directions: Measure wet ingredients into large bowl.
Add salt, yeast, rice, oats, corn meal, rye, optional ingredients, 2 cups white flour and 2 cups whole wheat flour; stir with wooden spoon.
Add 2 to 3 cups more whole wheat flour and stir until threads form on side of bowl.
Turn wet dough onto floured counter and knead in remaining flour; use bench knife to keep counter dry.
Work slowly to avoid too-dry dough (about 40 minutes).

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk.
Spoon over melted butter.
Heat fresh or canned fruit with sugar - adjusting less sugar for canned fruit.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350 for about 30 minutes or until crush is golden brown.
Crust will rise to the top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: watergate salad
directions: Gently mix all items together and chill.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, saute onion in butter or margarine for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes longer. Stir in water and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
In small bowl, stir cream and cornstarch.
Stir into mushroom mixture.
Stirring, bring to boil and boil 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Serve in individual bowls and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Spread nuts evenly over cake.
Melt and cool margarine and pour over nuts.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Cool in the pan. When cool, turn upside-down on serving tray.
Peel off wax paper and frost.

title: microwave cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook for 8 to 10 minutes on High in microwave.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 400° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool.

title: snack cracker
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil.
Add dill, garlic and lemon pepper.

title: night before french toast
directions: Use extra butter to grease 9 x 13 pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in one layer on the bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients, except butter.
When thoroughly mixed, pour over bread in pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours or overnight.
To bake, uncover pan, dot bread with butter and put into oven.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes until bread is puffy and lightly browned.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with syrup, honey, yogurt or sour cream with fresh fruit.
Leftovers are very good.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cream the sour cream and cream cheese together and spread in container and add taco sauce.
Chop and add remaining ingredients. Mix the lettuce, pepper and onion and then sprinkle grated cheese over the top and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cover the crushed cranberries with sugar, make the box of Jello according to pkg. and thicken slightly.
Add the celery and walnuts.
Yummmmm!!!

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature; dust dry Jell-O into cheese, leaving mixture lumpy.
Heat Coca-Cola to boiling and pour over cheese mixture.
Mix together, leaving some lumps.
Add nuts and pour into a small mold or dish.
Leave out of refrigerator 1 to 2 hours and salad will separate into layers. Cover and refrigerate to congeal.
A very unusual color and flavor, almost caramel maple.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash cakes
directions: Mix squash, onion, egg, salt and pepper to taste.
Add just enough flour to hold mixture together.
Spoon into hot skillet with oil and fry until brown and crisp on both sides.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in "ReaLemon" and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and the desired amount of glaze. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onions and potatoes, clams with the juices and clam juice.
Simmer until potatoes are done. Season with salt and pepper.
Mix flour with a little water; stir into chowder.
Add the cream.
Serve at once.

title: special "k" or rice krispie kookies
directions: Bring
sugar
and Karo to boil on stove and remove from heat. Stir
in
peanut
butter until melted.
Stir cereal in, about
2 cups at a time.
Work quickly as mixture will harden fast.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix the 2 cans of corn together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 11-inch or larger pan, layer scrambled meat, then corn mixture and potatoes.
Top with scrambled eggs.
Bake for one hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Fold in flour in four parts, being careful not to overbeat.
Add flavorings, lemon juice and rind.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan or double recipe and divide into 3 loaf pans.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick inserted in middle of cake comes out clean.

title: brownie ice cream delight
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brownie mix and bake 20 minutes at 350°, stirring after 10 minutes.
Remove 1 cup to save for topping.
Mix the rest of brownie crumbs with ice cream. Sprinkle reserved brownie on top.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over all.
Freeze 12 hours.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Cool and grate on coarse side of grater.
Melt butter and mix with onion, sour cream, salt and pepper. Fold mixture into potatoes.
Put in baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: real good candy
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in double boiler.
Stir a little to get all melted.
Stir in cashews and noodles.
Spoon by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: doughnut balls
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In a small bowl, mix together the oil, milk and egg.
Pour the liquid mixture over the dry ingredients and stir well.
Drop by teaspoon into deep, hot oil.
Cook about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain balls on paper towel.
Roll warm balls in confectioners sugar or mix up confectioners sugar glaze with milk and vanilla extract.

title: chili and sour cream dip
directions: Heat chili and stir in sour cream until blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sallie's cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and sprinkle with salt.
Place in refrigerator.
Mix all other ingredients.
Remove cucumbers from refrigerator and drain.
Mix everything together.
Refrigerate, stirring several times throughout the day before serving.

title: rainbow pasta-lobster salad
directions: In large pot, bring 4 cups of water to a boil; add pasta.
Cook until tender.
Rinse under cold water; set aside.
Cut up tomatoes (to desired size), cucumbers, green pepper, onion, yellow pepper and lobster or crab meat.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add Italian salad dressing to your taste.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator until ready for use.
Sprinkle with parsley on top.

title: stove top chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In large heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt butter; add cocoa and sugar, then milk and stir well.
Over medium heat, stirring frequently, bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oatmeal and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons onto foil or brown paper bag.
When cool, store airtight.
Great for classroom parties, bake sales and ball game snacks.
Makes about 24.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mammy's lazy man's pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and baking powder.	Add just enough sweet milk to make a thin batter.
Melt butter in 2-inch high pan.
Pour batter over melted butter.	Sweeten the fruit a little.
Then pour over batter.
Cook 30-40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6-8.
Wonderful!

title: zucchini spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
In mixer bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs until light and creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients just until combined, then fold in zucchini.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.

title: snooty squash
directions: Melt margarine in saute pan or skillet.
Add all ingredients except potatoes and tomatoes.
Boil diced potato while squash simmers.
Turn squash frequently after 7 or 8 minutes.
Drain potatoes and add with tomatoes to squash mixture.
Mix together and simmer 2 or 3 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve immediately as single dish meal with heated garlic or French bread.
(Cornbread ain't bad either.)

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips together.
Add other ingredients. Drop on wax paper a teaspoon at a time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and use to taste.

title: breakfast in a pan
directions: Mix corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put half of mix in pan.
Mark 4 areas with spoon and put raw egg in each area.
Spoon remaining mix over and around eggs.
Bake at 375° for 3 minutes, until mix raises over eggs.
Put on precooked sausages and continue baking 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm with margarine.

title: cajun buffalo wings
directions: Douse chicken wings with Tabasco sauce and sprinkle with pepper.
Grill on charcoal or gas grill.
Just before ready, baste with barbecue sauce.
Have plenty of tea or water handy; you'll need it.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Fill greased mini-muffin tins two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep about 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well in bowl and add nuts. Press half mix in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips and drizzle condensed milk.
Sprinkle rest of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, spread evenly.
Pour cherry pie filling next and spread evenly.
Pour yellow cake mix, right out of box, and spread evenly.
Put nuts on top.
Cut butter into pats and spread to cover entire cake.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: monterey jack and jalapeno turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter with minced cilantro. Roll out bread between 2 pieces of waxed paper until very thin. Brush bread lightly on both sides with melted butter mixture.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a meat fork.
Let it cool.
Crumble.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Combine and mix first five ingredients until smooth.
Add peas and carrots.
Set aside.
Place two triangles of the rolls together to form a rectangle.
Pinch the seams together.
Put one-fourth of the mixture in each of four rectangles.
Fold bread portion over chicken mixture to seal mixture inside.
Brush tops of rolls with butter and sprinkle with small amount of bread crumbs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until well browned on all sides.
(A combination of mild and hot sausage makes an extra flavorful dish.)
Pour off fat.
Add peppers, onion and oregano; toss with sausage and cook another 8 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the confectioners sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine together for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Layer bananas over cream mixture.
Drain strawberries and pineapple; put over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked chicken breasts and rice(serves 4)
directions: Spread uncooked rice in bottom of casserole; cover with undiluted soup.
Wash chicken breasts and lay on top of soup. Spread dry onion soup over top of raw chicken.
Pour 1 cup milk around edges.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
This is so easy and good enough for company.

title: houston's creamy cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Cover and chill for 4 hours.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water and bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces of chocolate chips (1 cup) and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: cheese-vegetable chowder
directions: Combine water, bacon, carrots and dry potatoes with sauce mix. Bring to a boil.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in large casserole.
Mash up Ritz crackers.
Melt oleo and put into cracker crumbs; pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, around 45 minutes.

title: chicken with artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Shake and dip in bread crumbs; brown in butter in frypan over medium heat.
Place golden browned chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking casserole.
Put cut-up artichoke hearts and sliced mushrooms over chicken.

title: dieters pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat egg yolks with salt until thick; add cottage cheese and flour, mixing lightly. Fold in egg whites.
Melt half the butter in skillet or on griddle.
Drop batter by spoonfuls onto skillet.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Add remaining butter as needed.
Serve with maple or fruit sauce.
Per serving: 115 calories.
Yields 6.

title: homemade relish
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, celery and salt.
Cover with water; let stand overnight, then drain.
Chop all vegetables in blender. Cook for 20 minutes, until relish consistency.
Stir regularly. Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Makes 8 jars of 16 ounces each.

title: simple potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender; peel and chop.
Combine potatoes, celery, chopped egg whites, pepper, mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl; mix gently.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with radishes and sliced egg whites.

title: lobster stew
directions: Simmer lobster meat in butter until it reaches a good pink color.
Slowly add milk and cream, stirring constantly until stew has developed a rich salmon color.
Remove from heat and let age 5 or 6 hours.
Reheat slowly.
Serves 8.

title: honey, thyme and yogurt dressing
directions: Whisk together yogurt, vinegar, honey, lemon juice, scallions, thyme, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup water.
Serve over assorted greens. Makes 2 cups.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook noodles until tender but still firm.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix Ricotta, egg, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Pour enough sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan to cover.
Fill shells with
cheese mixture.
Place in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: betty's peanut butter pie
directions: Whip
cream
cheese
until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar, peanut butter
and
milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Fold into pie crust and sprinkle with peanuts. Freeze. Take out 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate about 24 hours, no less than 4 hours. Remember to mix from time to time.

title: carrot salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine carrots, apples, raisins and walnuts.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour (bottom only) a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients and put in bottom of pan.

title: broil or fry hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 4 patties.
Broil or fry. Place patties on toasted buns.
Serve with tomatoes, lettuce and seasoning.

title: frances' beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar together well.
Slowly stir in room temperature beer.
Pour mixture into bread pan and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes really good toast!

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Thoroughly mix together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Chill dough.
Roll into small walnut sized balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown and still soft.

title: cornbread chili mix casserole
directions: Cook ground meat and drain.
Add soup and beans; set aside. Mix Jiffy corn muffin mix as per package directions.
Grease a small casserole dish.
Spread 2/3 corn muffin mix on bottom.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Spoon remaining corn muffin mixture over the meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Time and temperature of oven may vary with individual oven.

title: bar b que sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add all
other ingredients and bring to a slow boil for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican skillet spaghetti
directions: Heat a 12-inch electric skillet to 350°.
Brown turkey in a small amount of oil.
Remove turkey from pan and drain fat.
Put turkey back in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water, taco mix and instant onion.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Add spaghetti.
Reduce heat to 220°.
Simmer, covered, until spaghetti is tender, stirring frequently, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. This makes the equivalent of 1 (14 ounce) can.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except almonds, cheese and potato chips.
Gently pour
into
a greased 2 quart casserole. Stir in gently cheese
and	almonds.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve in pastry cups.

title: corncob syrup
directions: Boil cobs in 2 gallons water until soft.
Remove cobs; strain liquid.
Add sugar.
Boil down to 1 1/2 gallons.
Store in quart jars.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Put layer of chicken and layer of mixed ingredients in casserole dish.
Alternate layers.
Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: quick veggies
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, drain and crumble.
Add onion to 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook slowly until light brown.
Add seasoning, peas and cauliflower.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Garnish with bacon.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms, pat dry and remove stems.
Chop stems and combine sausage, garlic and parsley.
Cook until browned.
Drain grease off.
Stir in chopped stuffed mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: *If frozen blueberries, do not thaw.

title: meatball garden skillet
directions: Brown onion in butter until tender.
Beat the hamburger, flour, salt, pepper, egg and milk with fork until light and fluffy.
Add cooked onion and form in 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs over medium heat.
Remove from skillet and mix flour with drippings.
Add beef broth and water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add meatballs.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet, reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Pour boiling water over frozen peas to separate them; drain.
Add peas; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Mix peanut butter and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Press a chocolate kiss in the center.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tomato stew
directions: In a hot heavy bottomed pot or Dutch oven add bacon and onion. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring often until onion is soft and bacon is lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and Tabasco. Cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add the broken biscuits and cook 2 or 3 minutes more.
Taste and if too acidic, add sugar to balance flavors.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and bone from meat; cut into 4 to 6 serving pieces. Grease large skillet lightly with fat from meat.
Brown thoroughly on one side; turn and season with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt. Push meat to one side.
Add onions and cook and stir until tender. Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch with water; stir gradually into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add tomatoes.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nuts. Blend mayonnaise, sugar, juice and salt. Fold in whipped cream and fold into apple mixture. Chill. Serves 6.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Debone cooked chicken.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed together in mixing bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crushed crackers and margarine and pour over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Add all ingredients in saucepan, except meat.
Bring to a low simmer.
Add meat, if desired.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and brown sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine soda and sour cream. Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and
floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan; let cool completely on a wire rack.
Sift powdered sugar over top of cake, if desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cake mixes, melted butter, pie filling and nuts in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and mix together.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and margarine together.
Defrost frozen broccoli; drain.
Combine cheese mixture and broccoli in baking dish.
Crumble Town House crackers and make a covered layer over top of broccoli.
Bake in oven at 350° until crackers are golden brown.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw vegetables in shallow baking dish.
Mix can of soup, 1/2 package of cheese and sour cream with thawed vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until cheese is "bubbly."
Remove from oven and add remaining cheese.
Sprinkle French fried onions over top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted and onions are browned.

title: mom's cream cheese thumbprints
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Roll into balls and place in a 350° oven.
After 5 minutes, remove from oven and make a thumbprint in each cookie.
Continue to bake for 5 to 7 more minutes.
Cookies will not be brown.

title: cool hand luke
directions: Wash and drain strawberries.
Dip in Cool Whip.
Roll in Grape-Nuts and serve.
Delicious and easy!

title: low calorie lemonade
directions: *Sugar substitute is either 4 to 8 envelopes or 1 1/2 teaspoons or to taste.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.
Remove from oven and let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: salmon tomato loaf
directions: Mash salmon with a fork.
Mix remaining ingredients with salmon.
Pour into prepared baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: apple betty brown
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch square pan. In a large bowl, combine sugar, egg, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.

title: meringues
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until stiff peaks are formed. Drop onto greased baking sheet and bake for 2 hours at 250°. Serve with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic and mango and add salt and pepper. Cook macaroni, then add other ingredients.
Cut cheese into cubes. I usually save some cheese for the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250° to 300° until brown.

title: souper skillet pasta
directions: Microwave directions:
In a 3 quart casserole dish, heat ground beef for five minutes, drain.
Add tomatoes and Lipton soup mix and oregano blended with reserve liquid from the tomatoes and water.
Heat covered, for 5 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in uncooked macaroni and heat covered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Stir in parmesan cheese and top with Mozzarella cheese. Let stand covered for 5 minutes.

title: pecan drop cookies
directions: Mix butter until soft.
Mix in powdered sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rosalind's hot brie
directions: Place
Brie on ovenproof dish.	Spread honey on top and sides of Brie.
Cover with almonds.
Add more honey.
Place in preheated 350°
oven
until Brie softens.
Let cool slightly. Serve with crackers and apple slices.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and drain completely on paper towels.
Mix remaining ingredients together, stirring in Cool Whip last, just until mixed through.
Add grapes, mixing well.
Chill.

title: brown bag fruit mix
directions: Mix apple, banana and grapefruit sections with juice to prevent darkening of apple and banana.
Add grapes and pineapple and chill (fresh fruit in season may be substituted).
Makes 2 servings, 1 cup each.

title: reese's balls(candy)
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and sugar.
Roll into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Dip into chocolate with spoon or toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Spread mixture on rolled dough.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut in pieces and twist.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In medium size bowl, mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
This dip tastes great with strawberries!

title: caramel cream
directions: Add the flour to the white sugar.
To the eggs, add a little of the sugar mixture and then the scalded milk.
Then add the brown sugar and salt to taste.

title: candied citrus peel(easy method)
directions: Cut peel into long thin strips.
In a large kettle over high heat, heat peels and 8 cups of hot water to boiling; boil 15 minutes, drain and rinse.
Add 8 more cups hot water and boil 15 minutes and drain.
In same kettle over high heat, heat 1 3/4 cups sugar, the corn syrup and 1 1/2 cups water until boiling and sugar is dissolved, stirring frequently.
Gently stir in peels.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook until most of the syrup has been absorbed, about 40 minutes.
Remove from heat; gently stir in gelatin until dissolved and cool 10 minutes.
Onto wax paper place 1 cup sugar.
Lightly roll peels a few at a time in sugar adding more as necessary.
Place sugar coated peels in single layer on wire racks; let dry overnight.
Store in tightly covered containers.
Makes 8 cups.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Sprinkle slices with salt, allowing about 1 teaspoon for whole eggplant.
Pile slices on top of each other in a saucepan or baking dish, then place a weighted dish on top; let stand for 1 hour, then drain off the liquid that flows out.
Dip slices into a mixture of 1 beaten egg and 1/4 cup milk, then coat well with dry bread crumbs.
Fry over moderate heat until brown on both sides and thoroughly tender.

title: easy and good peanut butter pie
directions: Mix equal amounts of peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Put mixture in pie crust (save a small amount for top). Mix pudding, whipping cream and milk together.
Blend mixture until it thickens.
Put on top of peanut butter mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Top with remaining peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate. Tastes so creamy and smooth.

title: quick eggplant
directions: Peel and slice and eggplant. Coat both sides of the slices with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Dip each slice into a mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese until well coated.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until it browns.

title: baked carrots and celery
directions: Put carrots in casserole.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cover; bake until tender at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove cover for escape of excess moisture.

title: leftover turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and oleo until crumbly.
Add milk.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Mix soup and broth in dish. Add turkey.
Place flour mixture over top of soup mixture.
(May need to add more milk if flour mixture is too thick to pour.) Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut and wash broccoli florets.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add bacon and pour over broccoli.
Mix well.

title: spiced winter squash
directions: Mix the squash with the salt, coriander, mace, ginger and flour.
Turn into a buttered 1-quart shallow casserole dish. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
Mix the bread crumbs with the 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over the squash.
(Recipe may be made ahead to this point and refrigerated.) Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are golden and sugar has melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cream cheese cake
directions: Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. (Reserve 1 cup for topping.)
Add eggs and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes at high speed. Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: apple pudding
directions: Slice peeled apples in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, milk and flour. Add sifted baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla; spread over apples.

title: maxine's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
make	into
1 1/2-inch balls. Then roll in chopped salted peanuts.
If the first ingredients are a little sticky, add more powdered milk.
You can also add one of these
optional
ingredients:
raisins, coconut, chocolate	chips or Grape-Nuts to vary recipe.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Prepare jello using only 1 cup hot water.
Let cool.
Soften cream cheese with milk and add pineapple and nuts.
Mix with jello when cool.

title: easy dessert(chocolate)
directions: Soak cookies in milk and line like a crust in a 11 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
(Make the cookie soggy but not falling apart.)
On this layer, add a layer of Cool Whip.
Save a few cookies to crush and sprinkle on top.
Chill before serving.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Unwrap ice cream sandwiches and place in the bottom of a casserole dish, covering the bottom. Generously pour and smooth Cool Whip on top of sandwiches. Drizzle chocolate and caramel syrup toppings on top of Cool Whip. Randomly place cherries on top. Sprinkle with pecans. Cover with aluminum foil and freeze until ready to serve. ENJOY!

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes.
Beat vinegar, mustard, cayenne, salt and pepper until thick.
Add oil slowly while whisking.
Add scallions and dill weed.
Serve at room temperature.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute ground beef; set aside.
Combine peppers, onion and cheese.
Combine soda, salt, cornmeal, milk, corn and eggs. Grease iron skillet and heat.
Sprinkle small amount of meal in skillet and brown lightly.
Pour 1/2 batter into hot skillet. Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter.
Pour meat and onion mixture over this.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curried chicken ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, milk, salt and curry powder and pepper. Add the chicken, nuts and onion, mixing lightly; form into ball.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda three times. Put all ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into flat pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Grease pan with Crisco.

title: ray's smokey joe cake
directions: Mix butter, flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13 in. greased pan.
Cover entire pan.
Bake at 450 degrees until light brown. Cool in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, cool whip, and powdered sugar.
Spread over first layer.
Mix pudding mix, vanilla and milk.
Add to second layer.
Cover with cool whip and chopped pecans.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Blend together meat, onions, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls and cook in skillet until meat is cooked thoroughly. Combine soup and milk and pour over meatballs and bring to boil. Serve.

title: tropical macaroons
directions: Mix milk, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add the onion and garlic; stir-fry over medium-high heat about 2 minutes. Add the eggplant and stir-fry another 2 minutes. Add the zucchini, green pepper and tomatoes; stir-fry 3 minutes more. Add basil, salt and ground pepper. Cover and simmer 30 minutes over low heat. Uncover; stir gently and simmer 10 minutes. Add capers. Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: nonfat bean dip
directions: Stir all ingredients well and enjoy.

title: magic mustard sauce
directions: In a small bowl, blend mustard and water into a paste.
Pour paste in blender. Add remaining ingredients.
Process 1 minute. Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add grated cheese and Bisquick.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until they are done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Cream well and add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, sifted together, alternately with milk.
Add oats; stir in well.
Add raisins and nuts last.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Remove to rack.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Melt Velveeta in Manwich. Combine mixture with hamburger.
Serve with taco chips and dip.

title: prune puree
directions: Combine prunes and water in container of food processor. Process about 1 minute until pureed.
Puree may be covered and refrigerated up to 2 months.
Makes 2 cups.

title: raspberry delight
directions: In a bowl,
combine flour and sugar, blend in butter until smooth.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes
or until
set (crust will not brown).
Cool.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine sour cream, onions, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add cucumbers and mix well.
Chill.

title: stir fry veggies
directions: On medium, heat approximately 2 Tbsp. vegetable oil in wok or nonstick skillet.
Add vegetables one type at a time, stirring constantly.
When vegetable is slightly soft, add next vegetable until all are in pan except bean sprouts (add at end).
If necessary and it usually is, add chicken broth instead of more oil during vegetable cooking.
Make sure there is some liquid in the pan.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add bean sprouts and stir in seasonings and cover 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: donna's dump cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer the rest of the ingredients in order given. Top with the other stick of butter (melted). Bake at 350° for an hour or until done.

title: cantaloupe orange smoothie
directions: Blend cantaloupe, orange juice and lemon juice in a blender until smooth. Add 2 cups frozen yogurt and blend again until smooth. Serves 2.

title: opera cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk in a small sauce pan until thick like paste. Cool completely. While waiting for the flour paste to cool, cream together margarine and sugar in a mixing bowl and place in refrigerator. After paste is completely cooled, remove mixing bowl from refrigerator and add vanilla, beat mixture with an electric mixer until thick and smooth. Make sure all grains of sugar have dissolved. In hot weather, due to
the high margarine content, frosting should be refrigerated.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti noodles.
Drain and cool.
In large bowl, mix cottage or Ricotta cheese, 1 pound Mozzarella (cut up into bite-size pieces), eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Split noodles down the center.
Stuff with plenty of cheese; mix. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, seam side down.
Continue until all noodles are filled.
You will need another small pan also.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cook on 350° for 1 hour.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Put back in oven until melted.
Serve with meatballs and sausage.

title: two egg quick cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add shortening, vanilla and all but 1/3 cup of milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining milk.
Beat at medium for 1 minute.
Grease 2 deep 8-inch round cake pans.
Pour batter into cake pans and spread evenly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch cake layers.

title: california delight
directions: Save juices from oranges and pineapple cans.
Slice bananas and combine with all other ingredients, including juices.
Mix well and serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: oatmeal scotches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and water; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture; stir in oats, butterscotch bits, orange extract and nuts.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Be sure all lumps are smooth.
Add 3 cups of water; stir well.
Cook in double boiler or iron skillet until desired thickness is reached.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute the first 6 ingredients until very soft.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and green onion tops.
Stir just to mix and add soup and shrimp.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes over low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Steam salt pork in small amount of water until tender.
Add all ingredients, except pimentos.
Cook until almost tender.
Add pimentos.
Remove from heat.

title: seafood creole style(soup)
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, into hot salad oil, gradually stir flour; cook, stirring constantly, until flour is dark brown (mixture will be thick).
Add celery, green pepper and onion; cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are lightly browned, stirring constantly.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add and mix flour.
Add almond flavoring.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix together into a stiff dough.
Chill briefly.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters into desired shapes.
Poke a hole (near the top of each ornament) with a straw.
Let dry thoroughly (several days) on a rack.
Thread with a ribbon for hanging.

title: sausage en croute
directions: In covered 10-inch skillet over medium heat, simmer sausages and 1/4 cup water 5 minutes; uncover and cook sausages until browned, turning often. Refrigerate until cold.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Add enough flour (if needed) to handle easier.
Bake in moderate oven.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Whip until smooth. Slice bananas on pie crust.
Add filling and top with fruit pie filling.
Place extra Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over bottom of cooled pie crust.
(One large or 2 small pie crusts may be used.)

title: chinese sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and crumble; drain grease.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well, cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add sugar; stir.
Add half of flour and blend well.
Add egg, shortening and rest of the flour. Mix well.
Cover with damp towel and let rise in refrigerator at least 2 hours or overnight.
Take out as needed.
Roll out and let rise at room temperature.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: veggie bars
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press perforations together and spread close to edges of cookie sheet. Bake about 8 minutes at 375° and cool.

title: country ham and cranberries
directions: Insert cloves in
fat of the ham.
Wash cranberries and dry; mix with honey.
Pour
over ham and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1
hours or until ham is tender.
Baste occasionally with the liquid in the pan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy red beet soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart pot and simmer for 1 hour.

title: blueberry oat bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish. Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, nuts, baking soda and salt.
Add margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared dish.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Do not brown. Cool.
Add peppers, onions and olives.
Drain artichokes, reserving marinade.
Cut artichokes in half.
Combine marinade with curry and mayonnaise.
Add artichokes to rice and toss with dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into 3/4-inch cubes.
Melt butter in skillet and saute onion in it.
Roll beef in flour, then brown it in the cooked onion and butter.
Stir in the cream of mushroom soup, chicken broth and tomato paste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until all ingredients are completely mixed and heated through. Serve over cooked rice.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oranges together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts. Mixture will be thick and sticky.
Cook until nuts begin to pop.
Take off heat. Add soda and stir.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Shake to spread. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and egg. Mix well. Chill for 30 minutes. Spread mixture on cookie sheet and press down with fork. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aggie dip
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl with mixer the cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth, then add other ingredients, one at a time.
Mix until well mixed.
Place in covered bowl and chill until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal fruit squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the 2, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough into 5 balls.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling.
Dough can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days or can be wrapped in plastic or foil and frozen in balls until ready to use.
Dough will remain soft in refrigerator and can be taken out and rolled after waiting a couple of minutes.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into deep pie dish on top of unbaked crust.
Place butter on top.
It melts as pie bakes.
Pie mixture appears very thin when first placed in oven, but it thickens as it bakes.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour until crust is good and brown and pie is thickened and slightly brown.

title: cinnamon apple butter
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large kettle.
Cook on medium heat stirring often until cinnamon candy has all melted.
Place in pint jars or jelly jars and tighten lids.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, powder, onion and bell pepper.
Drain and add tomato paste; simmer.
Stir in remaining ingredients and stir. Cover; simmer 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli stir-fry
directions: Set out broccoli and cauliflower to thaw while preparing chicken.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
In large no stick pan or wok, brown chicken over medium heat.
After chicken is cooked, add bouillon, vegetables and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil, then turn down to medium heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 cups of cold water.
Add to chicken mixture.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave vidalia
directions: Cut onions crossways.
Place in dish. Top with butter, salt and pepper. Cook on High for 15 minutes.

title: whole cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Add cranberry sauce.
Mix together; put sour cream on top.
Swirl to marble.
Chill until firm.

title: my grandmother's stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1 1/4-inch pieces, roll in flour and brown in large pan with margarine.
Saute onions and mushrooms in drippings; add to meat with undiluted soup.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° until meat is tender, approximately 1 hour. In small pan, mix gravy mix, sour cream and wine.
Stir over low heat until well combined.
Add to casserole and serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, egg and pineapple juice over low heat until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Drain most of the juice from the sweet potatoes.
Whip so it is the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Mix in cream, eggs, butter and cinnamon.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar (fairly heavy) and pecans.
Drizzle with butter and honey.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set for 10 minutes to firm up.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add syrup and salt.
Beat well. Beat in	eggs
one
at a time; add pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake
in a 350° moderate oven for one hour and ten minutes, or until a knife comes out clean.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Beat together sweet potatoes, butter and sugar (use mixer). Next, work Bisquick in slowly with your hands.
(This will be very wet and moist.)
You must refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Form balls on greased cookie sheet.
Make small slits in balls for rolls. Cook in oven at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: rosy rhubarb cake
directions: Cut in shortening, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar as for pie crust.
Add milk and egg.
Mix together thoroughly and spread in bottom and a little up the sides of 9 x 13 cake pan. Top with rhubarb.
Sprinkle gelatin powder over top.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to high altitude directions on box. Bake 1/2 of the batter 20 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 15-inch pan.
Melt caramels, milk and butter over low heat.
Pour over first half of baked cake.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: carolina baked beans
directions: Cook beef and onions in small amount of oil in skillet.
Cook slowly until beef has turned white.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with Cool Whip and Jell-O.
Chill and serve.

title: easy pleasing meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a 13 x 9 inch baking dish with foil; coat with nonstick spray.
Mix meat, 1 cup water, stuffing mix, eggs and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce in a bowl until blended. Shape into a 9-1/2 inch long oval loaf; place in baking dish. Brush with remaining 1/4 cup sauce.
Bake 1 hour or until cooked through and a meat thermometer inserted in center registers at least 160°.

title: pineapple-orange squares
directions: Stir together flour, coconut, margarine or butter and brown sugar.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Press onto bottom of pan to form a firm, even crust.
Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: amish oven fried chicken
directions: Place oil and butter in shallow cooking pan and put in 375° oven to melt butter.
Set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies. Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together in one bowl, then in another bowl, mix pudding and milk. Blend in Cool Whip. Combine 2 bowls.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In a blender, blend onion, tomato sauce, cheese and taco seasoning.
Pour over meat and beans in an 8 x 10-inch microwave-safe pan.
Cover with crushed Doritos chips.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes. Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a blender, mix the butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add corn and milk; blend for about 30 seconds.
Pour ingredients into a buttered casserole; bake for 45 minutes.
Stir once halfway through cooking period. When done, a silver knife inserted in center will come out clean.

title: taco pie pizza
directions: Press biscuits into a 9 x 13-inch pan, forming crust.
Brown turkey, adding all other ingredients except peppers and cheese. Simmer 10 minutes; pour into unbaked crust, spreading evenly. Layer pepper rings and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 1/4 cups sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture.
Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually beat in the 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread meringue over top of pie, sealing in all the filling by touching all sides of the crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 4 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well, then add flour with soda.
Add oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Add more flour, if needed.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: lipton potato recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Add all ingredients in a bowl and toss until evenly coated. Empty potatoes onto a shallow baking pan. Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or tender and golden brown. Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serves about 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and peanut butter together.
Add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust and freeze.

title: mock pecan pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugars, syrup, butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until pies are set.

title: hazelnut-coated salmon steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place hazelnuts on baking sheet; bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Quickly transfer nuts to clean dry dish towel.
Fold towel; rub vigorously to remove as much of the skins as possible.
Finely chop hazelnuts using food processor, nut grinder or chefs knife.
Increase oven temperature to 450°. Place salmon in baking dish.
Combine apple butter, mustard, thyme and pepper in small bowl.
Brush on salmon; top each with nuts. Bake, nut side up, 14 to 16 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Melt Crisco
in
heavy	skillet and brown meat, onions, celery and peppers.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat
until meat is tender for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve on buns, toast or cooked rice.

title: layered garden salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and mustard.
Place all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order as listed.
Chill 8 to 10 hours before serving.
Keeps well for several days.
Be sure mayonnaise mixture covers entire top of salad.

title: sour cream dill sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours so flavors will mix.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine powdered sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla in a 2-quart microwavable casserole.
Put margarine on top in center of mixture.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add walnuts (if desired).
Pour into buttered, waxed paper-lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill for 30 minutes in freezer.
Cut into squares.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Take juices and use 1 cup.
Drain all fruit well.
Arrange in casserole.
Mix last 4 ingredients until well blended, free of lumps.
Pour over fruit.
Bake in 350° oven until liquid bubbles and fruit is hot.
Serves 10.

title: french apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon. Do not use electric mixer. Pour in oblong or Bundt pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: english toffee
directions: Place ingredients in pan and cook until deep beige in color. Stir constantly.
Pour into buttered dish and place 3 small Hershey bars over mixture.
Spread with knife and about 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Break into pieces when cooled.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
For cheese sauce, in a saucepan, melt butter.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add cubed cheese; stir until melted.
Stir macaroni into cheese sauce.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange tomato slices atop macaroni; sprinkle with a little salt.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: new england clam chowder casserole
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, saute bacon until crisp.
Add green onions and potatoes.
Saute for a few minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add clam juice or milk.
Stir to blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring, until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Finally, add clams with liquid and whipping cream.

title: apple-cornbread stuffing
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions, using 1 of the eggs and 1/3 cup milk.
Bake according to directions.
Set cornbread aside to dry out; this may be done the day before stuffing.

title: pot pie chicken or beef
directions: Mix the ingredients with enough water to hold the mix together and roll out thin on the table well floured so the dough won't stick.
Cut into squares.
Drop into chicken or beef broth until done (like noodles). Break pieces of chicken or beef when done. Stir meat through.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger in a 10-inch skillet.
Pour off grease and rinse with water.
Return skillet to burner.
Add remaining ingredients, including liquid from peas.
Add enough water to 1-inch from top of skillet.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until noodles are done.
Serve hot with salad, bread and butter for a balanced meal.
Enjoy.
Serves 4.

title: texas potato casserole
directions: Mix all but corn flakes and last 1/2 cup margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread corn flake mixture on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly delight (cookie)
directions: Mix butter, shortening, powdered sugar, vanilla and orange flavoring.
Add flour and pecans.
Shape in balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Combine corn syrup, sugar and oleo in a 2 cup microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir and microwave 1 1/2 minutes until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and soda. Pour over cereal and pecans, stirring to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool. Break into pieces.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine.
Cook for 6 minutes until boiling.
Stir ingredients. Drop on wax paper.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn in usual way, then pour it into a large brown shopping bag.
Place other ingredients into a 2-quart glass bowl, except soda and vanilla, and bring to a boil in microwave.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove and add the soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn in bag, mixing well.
Close top of bag and place in microwave. Cook on High for 90 seconds.
Remove bag and shake well.
Replace bag and repeat procedure 2 more times.
Place in large bowl and enjoy!

title: chicken livers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients and form into 25 to 30 small balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, turning once or microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
While still warm, add dressing and toss.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 1 tablespoon bacon grease until translucent.
Add all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: cabbage au gratin soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in next five ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute. Remove from heat and add the cheese.
Stir until melted.
Top with small crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom and sides for crust.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: baked potatoes
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put the potatoes, cut side down.
Melt butter and mix with cheese and dry dressing mix.
Pour over the potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 45 minutes.
Tear from bone and place in pan.
Add soup and water and stir.
Fix stuffing (by directions) and spoon on top of mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it boils and the sugar melts completely.
Remove from heat
and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Place
on
waxed
paper with a spoon or make balls with hands, if desired.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Set oven at 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan put in 1 stick oleo and place in oven to melt.
Combine all ingredients and pour over melted oleo.
Spoon on fruit.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
Crush saltines; add to eggplant and onion mix.
If you need, you can add more crackers.
Then stir in cheese and mushroom soup.
Place in a greased ovenproof dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
You may also sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serves 8.

title: saucey chicken
directions: Cook chicken in a little water until done. Season with salt and garlic.
Add sauce; simmer a minute or two. Cut off heat and top with cheese.

title: best macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased (with margarine) crock-pot and top with remaining cheese. Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours or up to 6 hours for a golden crust.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Add flavoring. Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar, beating until smooth. Add egg yolks; continue beating. Combine flour, salt and soda. Add alternately with buttermilk, then stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool completely before frosting.

title: gooey bars (crunchy)
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top, sprinkle pecans and butterscotch, chocolate and peanut butter chips.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray Pam in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped pecans.
Spread coconut next.
