Mix box cake mix with milk, oil and 3 eggs.
Pour over coconut.
In microwave, melt butter and cream cheese, add powdered sugar.
(May have to add a little more milk and drizzle over cake mix.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Blend together. Best if you use Granny Smith apples. Probably will keep for 1 week.

title: festal pumpkin bars
directions: In a bowl, sift together all dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In second bowl, cream sugar and oil. Add eggs and pumpkin.
Cream. Add dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 18-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Mix butter beans, juice included, stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add to beef and onion mixture.
Put in baking dish and cover with cheese.
Mix cornbread by directions on package.
Cover top of casserole with cornbread mixture.
Then bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: easy way to cook fruit pie fillings(cherry, blueberry, peach, rhubarb)
directions: Mix together in a 2 to 3-quart glass mixing bowl; microwave on High until almost thickened (stirring occasionally).
Pour into unbaked pie shell; add a pat of butter and cover with top crust. Bake in regular oven at 350° for 30 minutes until crust is browned.
Fruit fillings will always be done if made this way.

title: lemon lime bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs, baking powder, brown sugar, vanilla, flour, salt and nuts.
Spread over baked crust and return to oven and bake 20 minutes.
Cook lemon pudding as directed on package except add 1/4 cup extra water.
Cook until thick.
Add lime Jell-O.
Mix until blended.
Spread over baked bars. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve.
Cut into squares with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Take chicken off bone; cut in bite-size pieces. Saute onions and celery in margarine. Heat broth and soups and pour over breadcrumbs. Add onions and celery. Mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Pour half in greased 3-quart casserole dish. Add chicken and top with rest of dressing. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Beat all ingredients (except cherry pie filling) in large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pans. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Prepare whipped cream.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Spoon 1/2 pie filling on top about 1/2-inch from edge.
Top with second cake.
Spoon remaining pie filling to within 1/2-inch of edge. Frost edge and sides with whipped cream; spoon edging around top border.
Keep refrigerated.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix together and put 2/3 of the batter in 9x13 pan.
Cook at 350° for six minutes.
Melt 14 oz. Kraft caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over cooked batter and sprinkle 6 oz. milk chocolate chips and the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until done.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Stir eggs, cake mix and oil together.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts, etc., if desired.
Using a teaspoon, drop spoonfuls of batter onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and watch them disappear!

title: coconut or banana cream pie
directions: Use same filling for both pies; put bananas on top of baked pie crust before adding filling.

title: pear zucchini bread
directions: Spray two 8x4x2 inch baking pans with nonstick coating.
In a medium mixing bowl combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda, baking power and salt.
In a large mixing bowl combine pears, sugar, zucchini, oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stir just till combined.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove bread from pan.
Wrap in plastic when thoroughly cool and store overnight before slicing.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and salad oil.
Add vanilla, baking powder, cinnamon and half the flour.
Beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: philly avocado dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and avocados.
Mix until well blended. Stir in lemon juice, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand 30 minutes.
Bring to boil about 10 minutes, put in jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix by hand and form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut the potatoes in halves or quarters and place them in a baking dish with the whole cloves of garlic and onions and a small amount of water.
Toss with rosemary. Cover pan and bake for 20 minutes, then remove the cover and roast for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: skunk shampoo(household hints)
directions: Mix peroxide, soap and baking powder.
Pour a generous amount on animal.
Lather up.
Leave on for 3 to 4 minutes.
Rinse and repeat.
Do not store excess.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook potatoes, mixed vegetables, onion and stewed tomatoes.
Add seasonings to taste.
When vegetables are done, add cheese.
Served with cornbread, makes a meal.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook meat and place in crock-pot.
Add chili to meat.
Cut Velveeta into small pieces and melt in microwave.
When it is melted, add to meat and chili.
Mix well.
Keep warm and serve with Tostitos or your favorite chip.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse beans, peas and corn, then combine in a bowl with onions, green pepper and celery.
Combine honey, vinegar, oil and seasonings.
Heat just enough to blend and pour over beans. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and milk; let cool.
Add warm water to yeast in small bowl and let set for 5 minutes.
Add yeast to cool mixture and blend 3 cups of flour.
Add eggs and salt.
Mix in 3 more cups of flour and pour in greased bowl.
Cover until doubled (about 2 hours).
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise until double again on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
This recipe can also be used for cinnamon rolls.

title: rice krispies balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cereal, nuts and coconut, in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to slow boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Have cereal and nuts in large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over cereal.
Mix well.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add crabmeat and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute. Serve over rice and garnish with chow mein noodles.
Serves 3.

title: hot, quick soup
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, vegetables and juice and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender. Add rice, stir, bring to a boil and cover.
Turn off burner and let set for 15 minutes. Add seasoning.

title: portuguese doughnuts
directions: Heat oil or fat (2 to 3-inches) to 375° in deep fryer or kettle.
Stir together Bisquick, milk, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Dip bread in batter.
Fry in hot oil or fat until golden brown, drain and roll in sugar.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 3 dozen doughnuts.
(Very good.)

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix together and let stand in warm room for 8 hours.

title: strawberry cake frosting
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar. Gradually add strawberries until mixed, then beat until smooth.

title: creamy salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and flour.
Stir dry ingredients into eggs.
Heat vinegar, water and butter.
When butter is melted, remove from heat.
Quickly pour in egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to heat, cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened (about 3 minutes).
Cool and keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Approximately 1/2 to 3/4 pound meat per person.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple. Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all together in a large bowl until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix together butter, shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in the water and vanilla.
Sift flour and add the flour, baking powder, salt and soda to the butter mixture.
Add moist coconut. Roll into balls.
Flatten each ball with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: breakfast surprise cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo. Add eggs and cream.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Put 3/4 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread fruit over top of batter.
Drop rest of batter by spoonfuls over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until browned. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or powdered sugar and milk glaze.

title: fried deer steak(my son, tracy, cooks this)
directions: Soak deer steak, covered in water, in refrigerator overnight. Change water 2 or 3 times.

title: bread stuffing for turkey or chicken
directions: Put oil in a large skillet; add celery, onions, salt and pepper and saute until tender.
Put bread cubes into a large bowl or pan and set aside.
In another bowl, break eggs and add 1 1/2 cups of water.
Stir together and pour over bread.	Next, take celery and onions and add 2 1/2 cups of water; pour over bread and eggs.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Add mixed dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.
After bread has cooled 15 minutes, spoon on glaze.
Remove from pan after 10 additional minutes.

title: herbed spinach
directions: Press excess water from spinach.
Combine with next 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased baking dish. Toss stuffing mix with butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: new generation polish pierogi
directions: Boil shells until cooked.
Boil potatoes until done.
Drain, peel and mash.
Add Cheddar cheese to potatoes and 1 stick of oleo and mix well until blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill shells to capacity with mixture and arrange in a shallow pan in a single layer.
Cook chopped onion in 3 sticks of oleo until wilted (not brown).
Then spoon over filled shells.
Cover pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) round pans. Prepare pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and 1/4 cup Kahlua.
Chop candy bars into chunks and defrost topping.
When cake has cooled, cut into 4 (8-inch) circles.
In a large bowl, layer:
cake, pudding, topping and candy.
Repeat layers.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: toasted coconut rice
directions: Toss hot cooked rice with melted butter or margarine and coconut, which has been toasted on a cookie sheet under your broiler to a medium brown.

title: lima beans
directions: Heat large saucepan. Spray with cooking spray. Saute onions until tender. Pour in chicken broth, bring to boil. Add beans and enough water to cover. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana oat pecan bread
directions: Oil 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon on waxed paper or in bowl.
Slice bananas into a medium bowl; beat with electric mixer.
Add flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Stir in oats and pecans.

title: low calorie frozen treat
directions: Place in blender.
Blend until you get a smooth icy mixture. Makes 4 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken 'n que sauce
directions: Mix in a bowl and let stand at least 1 hour.
Pour over chicken and let stand at least 1 hour or in the refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally.
May also be used to baste the chicken while grilling.

title: new york cheese cake(diabetic)
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, margarine and 1 tsp. Equal for Recipes or 3 packets Equal sweetener or 2 Tbsp. Equal Spoonful in bottom of 9-inch spring form pan. Reserve 1 Tbsp. crumb mixture. Pat remaining mixture evenly on bottom and 1/2 inch up side of pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until crust is lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Cool on rack.

Beat cream cheese and 5 1/2 tsp. Equal for Recipes or 18 packets Equal sweetener or 3/4 c. Equal Spoonful in large bowl until fluffy; beat in eggs, egg whites and cornstarch. Mix in sour cream and vanilla until well blended. Pour mixture into crust. Place cheesecake in roasting pan on oven rack, add 1 inch hot water to roasting pan. Bake in preheated 300° oven just until set in the center, 45 to 60 minutes. Remove cheesecake from roasting pan, sprinkle with reserved crumbs and return to oven. Turn oven off and let cheesecake cool 3 hours in oven with door ajar. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. remove side of pan; place cheesecake on serving plate.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate. Serve.

title: pea soup
directions: Shell green peas.
Wash the peas and put them in a soup kettle.
Cover with cold water.
Boil 20 minutes.
Take out 1 cup and press the remainder through the puree sieve.
Return the soup to the kettle and add milk and 1 cup of peas.
Rub butter and flour until smooth; stir into the soup and stir continually until the soup is thick and smooth.
It should be the consistency of thick cream.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: spinach crescents
directions: Separate rolls out of can and cut each crescent in half. Brush one side with oil and sprinkle with cheese.
In a bowl, combine remaining seasonings, spinach and mayonnaise.
Put 1 teaspoonful on each triangle. Roll triangle of dough, wide end first, into smaller end.
Pinch end and bend into a curve.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Makes 16 to 20 rolls.

title: tomato, basil on pasta
directions: Scald tomatoes in boiling water; chop finely and put in bowl. Add basil, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and oil.
Mix well and let sit 1 hour at room temperature.
Cook linguini.
Drain.
Toss lightly with tomato mixture.
Add cheese.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chicken michelle
directions: Wash mushrooms and cut in half or slice.
Saute them in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove them temporarily.
Add remaining butter; melt.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and brown thoroughly. Return mushrooms to pan.
Sprinkle all with tarragon.
Add wine. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and mushrooms to plate. Stir sour cream into juices (use a whisk to keep it smooth).
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with chives and serve.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix cherry filling and condensed milk.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in freezer.

title: crab meat cakes
directions: Melt butter and saute pepper and onion until soft. Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Blend in flour. Scald milk and add, stirring until thick. Add crab meat. Chill thoroughly. Form into round cakes 1-inch thick.
Dip cakes in cracker meal, then dip in beaten egg, then dip in bread crumbs. Fry in deep fat until brown. Delicious plain or served with shrimp or oyster sauce.

title: chow chow
directions: Cook 3 minutes.
Seal in jars while hot.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix and refrigerate, kneading once a day, for 3 days.
Shape into rolls and bake for 10 hours at 150°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix as you would a cake and pour into two greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: apple pie filling cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Combine beaten eggs, vanilla, oil, nuts and raisins.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apple pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli well. Mash. Mix eggs, margarine, soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Put butter and chopped onion in casserole.
Heat until butter is melted.
Add beef broth/bouillon and mushrooms (sliced and drained).
Add raw rice.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese crescent(chimichanga)
directions: Put turkey with legs facing you.
Put fork in breast.
Cut between thigh and body to joint.
Cut through joint.
Cut between thigh and drumstick to separate.
Slice meat away from bone on drumstick and thigh.
Put fork in upper wing.
Make a horizontal cut above wing joint to remove wing.
Cut through to wishbone. Slice 1/8-inch thick slices straight down breast, beginning 1/2 way up breast section.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put garlic in hot jars.
Pack okra tightly in the jars. Sprinkle dill seed over top of okra.
Cut some off top of okra before packing, but do not cut down to seed pod.
Bring vinegar, salt and water to full boil; simmer a few minutes, until all salt is dissolved.
Pour boiling mixture over okra and seal jars immediately.
(The vinegar, salt and water make enough liquid for 6 pints.)

title: persimmon squares
directions: Sprinkle soda over persimmon pulp.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake in jelly roll pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with light frost or glaze.

title: tea cookies(paximathia 1)
directions: Mix eggs
and
sugar
in
electric mixer for 5 minutes. Slowly add oil.
Then
add
the lemon rind and finally add the flour and keep
mixing until blended well.
Pour into shallow pan, which has been lined with oiled wax paper.
The uncooked mixture should be	3/4-inch
thick;
it will rise when baked. Bake in a
350° oven
for
minutes or until golden brown. Remove pan
from oven and slice each piece into strips, about 3/4-inch wide.
Place each
piece
on
its side and return to oven for about 5 minutes until golden brown.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Delicious as a salad or dessert.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, squash, sour cream, carrot, salt and pepper.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Layer squash and bread crumbs twice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pasta salad(for 25)
directions: Cook orzo macaroni until done.
Rinse with cold water. Combine all ingredients in very large bowl.
Mix well.
Reserve a few grape halves to decorate top of salad.

title: pioneer cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and flatten with glass or fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mother's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each one.
Stir flour in all at once.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nut meats.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° for about 1 hour.
(A good way to get rid of tired bananas.)

title: scotcheroos
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup and heat in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and mix in vanilla and peanut butter. Stir in rice crispies.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: country roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with 1/2 the onion, entire envelope Lipton onion soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Also salt and pepper to your desire.
Cover roast with tinfoil.
Place in roasting pan with potatoes, carrots and the other half of the onion.
Cover to top of roast with water. Cover pan and cook at 300° for 3 1/4 to 4 hours.

title: dirty rice or spicy cajun rice
directions: Cook gizzard in pressure cooker at 15 pounds pressure for 12 minutes or boil in pot until tender.
Remove from pot, saving broth for further use.
Chop gizzards and set aside.
In a 3-quart pot, cook rice as follows:
Add rice, bouillon cubes, water and 1 cup of reserved broth.
Stir at high heat until it begins to boil, then, reduce heat to medium low and cook with lid until rice is almost done, uncovered.
While waiting, in a large pot brown ground turkey, then add chopped chicken gizzard, onion, celery, garlic and chopped peppers.
Saute about 3 minutes, then simmer with lid on pot about 10 minutes.
Then when water has evaporated from rice, add rice to meat mixture, continuing to simmer, adding cayenne pepper and salt.
Cook until rice is done, stirring occasionally.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in half.
Crumble half of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread half of the pudding over cake.
Spread half of cherry pie filling, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Repeat for second layer and then refrigerate.

title: spiral pasta salad(0 g. fat)
directions: Combine the pasta, fat-free Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Toss with the vegetables.
Serve cold.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch diameter beach pail and a trowel.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed pepper cups (red)
directions: Note: For crisp peppers omit precooking peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.

title: homemade crescent rolls(my "good old" 4-h recipe)
directions: Mix the first three ingredients; let stand for five minutes. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; divide into eight parts. Roll each part into a circle; divide into sixths or eighths. Brush with melted butter.
Starting with wide end, roll into crescents.
Let rise again until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white to a stiff froth.
Mix sugar, flour and salt. Add to egg white gradually.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ice screamers
directions: Melt the ice cream and sherbet together; mix well.
Add the soda and vodka (more or less to taste).
Mix well in a punch bowl or just in gallon containers.
May add cherries and ice cubes for pretty appearance.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and chicken broth and set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish layer stuffing, chicken and soup mixture, ending with stuffing on top.
Melt margarine and our over the top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add 2/3 cup powdered sugar; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; add to butter mixture, beating until mixture forms a dough.
Divide dough into 5 equal parts.
Shape 1 part of dough into a 9-inch-long cylinder; roll in powdered sugar.
Place shaped dough on an 11 x 4-inch strip of wax paper.
Transfer wax paper with dough to a microwave-safe cookie sheet or a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Press 9 pecan halves or cherry halves in a row on top of dough; flatten dough evenly.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt and stir until smooth. Add 1 1/2 cups nuts and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Pour into square pan. Chill 3 hours.

title: kraut
directions: Grate cabbage and pack in jars tightly.
For a quart add 1 tsp canning salt, 1 tsp sugar.
Pour boiling water over cabbage.
Take a knife and put holes to let water go down through the cabbage and cover completely and seal.
Put jars in a bowl or pan lined with a towel the kraut will work out.
Pint:
1/2 tsp canning salt; 1/2 tsp sugar.

title: bill's favorite hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion and brown meat.
Add drained beans, soup and egg. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes and strips of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
(Also good for dumping in small portions of any leftover veggies.)

title: antipasto pasta salad with chicken or salami
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.
In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add macaroni and toss well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.
A great summer dish for outside party.

title: cheese-bacon potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thick.
Combine mayonnaise and cream.
Add Blue cheese and fold into potatoes.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve immediately.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: *Any fruit flavor yogurt can be substituted for lemon yogurt.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Mix well.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: grandma's christmas salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: king's ranch casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients together with only half of cheese. Make a layer
of
tortillas
and
layer
of chicken mixture in casserole. Sprinkle rest
of cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: orange fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add the juice and rind to the yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Add the water and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks, adding 2 tablespoons sugar.
Fold into dressing.
Good on fruit or congealed salad.

title: opossum pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.
For filling, mix next 3 ingredients until creamy and spread over cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups of milk and spread over cheese filling.
Mix chocolate pudding with remaining milk and spread over the vanilla pudding.
Spread top with remaining Cool Whip.
Shave Hershey bar on top, if desired.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix all together and chill.
You may use any fruit or jello you like.

title: minnesota dessert
directions: Make cake and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and milk.
When this becomes smooth add pudding mix and beat, when it gets thick spread over cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding mixture, then spread Cool Whip over this and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: english spiced tea
directions: Combine honey, cloves, cinnamon, and orange slices in saucepan with water.
Stir and bring to full boil.
Add tea and serve in 8 mugs.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Store in container.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Break salmon into chunks.
Place half of the chunks in the bottom of a well-greased casserole.
Mix the remaining salmon in casserole.
Put the remaining salmon on top.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put in a nonstick skillet; cook for 1 hour.
Take out every 30 minutes to drain grease from pan.
Serves 8 people.

title: manhattan potatoes
directions: Combine the cooked potatoes, onions, green peppers and pimento in casserole dish.
Melt the butter and mix with the soup and milk.
Pour over the potatoes.
Finally, top the potatoes with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with 1 tablespoon sugar. Scald milk and let cool.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and flour to handle.
Knead until not sticky.
Let rise until light.
Knead down; let rise again.
Make into buns and let rise.
Bake plain rolls at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This is a good basic dough even for sweet rolls.
If used for sweet rolls, follow the recipe except when used with a sugar-butter coating try a 350° to 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bottoms are lightly browned in glass pan.
(This can be used very well with Rapidmix method of Fleischmann's.)

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine ingredients and fry by tablespoon in hot oil.

title: smothered pork chops and sweet potatoes
directions: In large dutch oven, saute onions in oil.
Add meat.
Cover with lid and cook, stirring occasionally until the meat is done. Add sweet potatoes.
Cook with lid on until potatoes are done.

title: shrimply delicious
directions: Rinse shrimp and pat dry.
In
a single layer, place in a 3 quart oblong
casserole.
Lightly sprinkle all the seasonings in order listed.
Cut
butter
into
chips and place over the seasoned shrimp.
Shake or drizzle Wish-Bone Italian salad dressing over all the
shrimp.
Generously
sprinkle the bread crumbs so that each shrimp
is
well
coated.
Bake
at
350°, uncovered, for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, water and syrup.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Add peanuts gradually so mixture continues to boil.
Continue to cook, stirring often, to 260° on a candy thermometer or until a teaspoon of the mixture dropped into very cold water forms a ball that is elastic but hard enough to hold shape.
Then add butter and cook until it spins hard and brittle thread.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in soda.
Pour on cookie sheets.
Spread.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saut onion in oil until tender. Stir in chicken, cream of chicken soup and 1 can green chilies. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese; roll up tortilla. Place in a lightly greased dish. Spread Cheddar cheese soup over this and then top with remaining shredded cheese and green chilies. Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes; uncover and bake for 5 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Make it the night before and put in freezer.
Take it out 2 hours ahead of time, then add 7-Up.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing and butter together and put
in a buttered casserole.
Mix stuffing, 1 cup of hot water and
butter.
Sprinkle
over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with margarine.
Mix water, celery soup, chicken soup and rice; pour into casserole dish or pan.
Layer chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cherry delights
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Blend in Karo and egg yolks. Add flour and mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in finely chopped nuts. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press candied cherry halves into centers. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: diet ice cream
directions: Mix well and put in freezer.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter, add celery, onion, 1 can broth and spices.
Cook until celery and onions are tender.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in pan with onion and green pepper, then add tomato juice.
Let simmer 1/2 hour; add corn.
Put macaroni (uncooked) in baking dish.
Pour hot mixture over.
Pour can of tomato soup on top.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tossed salad with roquefort dressing
directions: Toss all of the ingredients.
Serve with dressing on the side.

title: sugar n' spice cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, egg and molasses together.
Mix in flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir thoroughly.
Roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mash crackers; add nuts and fruit.
Melt marshmallows, butter and cream.
Add dry ingredients (it will be hard to mix, but make sure to get all dry ingredients mixed well).
Take the box that the crackers came out of and line it with waxed paper.
Use this to put the cake back in.
Seal it with more waxed paper and put in refrigerator until the next day.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
In saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa and shortening.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add water, eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla to sugar and flour mixture and mix well.
Blend in chocolate mixture and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground cranberries and sugar together; let set in refrigerator overnight.
Add marshmallows and pecans; stir in whipping cream just before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift first three ingredients into a bowl.
Add egg; mix lightly with fork until mixture is crumbly. Arrange fruit pieces in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Top with crumbs.
Pour butter over top of crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 40 minutes or until crumbs are crisp.

title: 24-hour sliced pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and canning salt and let sit 1 hour or so (you can use an ice cream pail for this).
Boil and cool sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Then pour over cucumbers. Mix together and let set overnight.
Can eat in 24 hours. Refrigerate and put in containers.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup mix. Mix well and form into 6 steaks. Place in baking dish and bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes until done.
Add additional shredded cheese on top until melted.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form bite-size balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve on warming tray or chafing dish.
Easily frozen and re-warmed.
Makes 100 balls.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup butter and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Top with corn flakes mixture just before baking.

title: fettucine with white sauce #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook noodles. Drain and set aside. Heat butter in skillet. Saute onion. Stir in red pepper, tuna and seasonings to taste. Pour in dissolved chicken bouillon. Heat to boiling. Remove from heat and stir in cream, half of the chopped parsley and half of the grated cheese. Blend in tuna mixture with noodles and place in Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: macaroni stroganoff(quick and easy!!)
directions: Boil macaroni per box instructions.
Brown ground beef, onion and seasonings.
Combine macaroni and ground beef.
Stir in soup; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and peas.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: *Can saute these in 1 stick oleo.

title: mountain man's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot.
Use medium size bowl.
May buy already mixed shredded cabbage at Kroger's.
Dice apples.

title: chocolate-mint trifle
directions: Bake cake as instructed for 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut cake into 16 pieces (once lengthwise and then into 8 pieces).
Split the 16 pieces in half lengthwise.
Fill bottom of trifle bowl (or other large glass bowl) with cake.
Spread layer of 1 package prepared pudding over cake.
Drizzle creme de menthe over pudding. Add peppermint extract and food coloring to Cool Whip.
Spread almost half over the pudding.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with slivered Andes candies, chocolate-mint jimmies or any other garnish.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk and mix in the rest of the ingredients. Shape into small balls and brown in shortening.
Drain meatballs on paper towel and pour grease from frypan.
In the same pan, prepare the Sauce.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil 5 minutes, stirring.
Pour over 4 quarts popcorn and shape into balls.
May add peanuts.

title: halibut caddy ganty
directions: Cut halibut
in
serving
sized
pieces and marinate in wine for 2 hours.
Drain and pat dry.
Roll them each in bread crumbs. Place them in
a
single
layer in a baking dish that can be brought to	the table.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread
this
sauce over the fish, smoothing it out to the edges
of
pan.
Sprinkle
the top with paprika. Bake at 500° for 15	to
20	minutes
or until light brown and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Brown the pork chops well.
Remove from pan.
Add soup to drippings.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add to soup and stir well.
Add onion and rice.
Mix well.
Pour rice into casserole and top with browned chops.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
